{"title_page": "Anna Francisca de Bruyns", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = Wenceslas Hollar - Anna Francisca de Bruyns (State 2).jpg\n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = A portrait of Anne Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns, aged 24, engraved by [[Wenceslas Hollar]].\n| native_name      = Anne Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns\n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = <!--only use if different from name-->\n| birth_date       = 1604 <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living artists, {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} for dead -->\n| birth_place      = \n| death_date       =  1675 <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> \n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| nationality      = \n| education        = Probably taught by her uncle, [[Jacob Franquart|Jacques Francquart]] \n| alma_mater       = \n| known_for        = portraits\n| notable_works    = \n| style            = \n| movement         = \n| spouse           = [[Isaac Bullart]]\n| patrons          = [[Isabella Clara Eugenia]]\n| memorials        = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} -->\n| module           =\n}}\n'''Anna Francisca de Bruyns''' (1604, in [[Morialm\u00e9]] &ndash; 1675, in [[Arras]]) was a Flemish Baroque painter.\n\n==Biography==\nShe was the niece of architect [[Jacob Franquart|Jacques Francquart]], who probably taught her to paint.<ref>A. Siret, \"Bruyns (Anne Fran\u00e7oise de)\", ''[[Biographie Nationale de Belgique]]'', [https://web.archive.org/web/20161220081745/http://www.academieroyale.be/academie/documents/FichierPDFBiographieNationaleTome2044.pdf vol. 3] (Brussels, 1872), 123\u2013128.</ref> She was painting by the age of seventeen. She is said to have surpassed many painters of her time.<ref name=Houbraken>{{in lang|nl}} [http://www.dbnl.org/tekst/houb005groo01_01/houb005groo01_01_0076.htm Anna Francisca de Bruyns Biography] in ''De groote schouburgh der Nederlantsche konstschilders en schilderessen'' (1718) by [[Arnold Houbraken]], courtesy of the [[Digital library for Dutch literature]]</ref>\n\nShe did some work for the Infanta [[Isabella Clara Eugenia]].<ref name=RKD>[http://explore.rkd.nl/explore/artists/13695 Anna Francisca de Bruyns] in the [[RKD]] database</ref> At some point between 1622 and 1629, when the couple set up house in [[Arras]], she had married the Rotterdam writer [[Isaac Bullart]]. They had 12 children.<ref name=RKD/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* M. Benisovich, \"Biographie d'Anne-Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns, peintre, ecrite par Jacques Ignace Bullart son fils\", ''Oud-Holland'' 68 (1953), pp.&nbsp;179\u2013182\n* [http://www.artnet.com/artists/anna-francisca-de-bruyns/past-auction-results Anna Francisca de Bruyns] on [[Artnet]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bruyns, Anna Francisca de}}\n[[Category:1604 births]]\n[[Category:1675 deaths]]\n[[Category:Flemish Baroque painters]]\n[[Category:Belgian women painters]]\n[[Category:People from Florennes]]\n[[Category:17th-century women artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = Wenceslas Hollar - Anna Francisca de Bruyns (State 2).jpg\n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = A portrait of Anne Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns, aged 24, engraved by [[Wenceslas Hollar]].\n| native_name      = Anne Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns\n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = <!--only use if different from name-->\n| birth_date       = 1604 <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living artists, {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} for dead -->\n| birth_place      = \n| death_date       =  1675 <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> \n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| nationality      = \n| education        = Probably taught by her uncle, [[Jacob Franquart|Jacques Francquart]] \n| alma_mater       = \n| known_for        = portraits\n| notable_works    = \n| style            = \n| movement         = \n| spouse           = [[Isaac Bullart]]\n| patrons          = [[Isabella Clara Eugenia]]\n| memorials        = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} -->\n| module           =\n}}\n'''Anna Francisca de Bruyns''' (1604, in [[Morialm\u00e9]] &ndash; 1675, in [[Arras]]) was a Flemish Baroque painter.\n\n==Biography==\nShe was the niece of architect [[Jacob Franquart|Jacques Francquart]], who probably taught her to paint.<ref>A. Siret, \"Bruyns (Anne Fran\u00e7oise de)\", ''[[Biographie Nationale de Belgique]]'', [https://web.archive.org/web/20161220081745/http://www.academieroyale.be/academie/documents/FichierPDFBiographieNationaleTome2044.pdf vol. 3] (Brussels, 1872), 123\u2013128.</ref> She was painting by the age of seventeen. She was claimed to have been better than all other women painters of her time.<ref name=Houbraken>{{in lang|nl}} [http://www.dbnl.org/tekst/houb005groo01_01/houb005groo01_01_0076.htm Anna Francisca de Bruyns Biography] in ''De groote schouburgh der Nederlantsche konstschilders en schilderessen'' (1718) by [[Arnold Houbraken]], courtesy of the [[Digital library for Dutch literature]]</ref>\n\nShe did some work for the Infanta [[Isabella Clara Eugenia]].<ref name=RKD>[http://explore.rkd.nl/explore/artists/13695 Anna Francisca de Bruyns] in the [[RKD]] database</ref> At some point between 1622 and 1629, when the couple set up house in [[Arras]], she had married the Rotterdam writer [[Isaac Bullart]]. They had 12 children.<ref name=RKD/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* M. Benisovich, \"Biographie d'Anne-Fran\u00e7oise de Bruyns, peintre, ecrite par Jacques Ignace Bullart son fils\", ''Oud-Holland'' 68 (1953), pp.&nbsp;179\u2013182\n* [http://www.artnet.com/artists/anna-francisca-de-bruyns/past-auction-results Anna Francisca de Bruyns] on [[Artnet]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bruyns, Anna Francisca de}}\n[[Category:1604 births]]\n[[Category:1675 deaths]]\n[[Category:Flemish Baroque painters]]\n[[Category:Belgian women painters]]\n[[Category:People from Florennes]]\n[[Category:17th-century women artists]]\n", "name_user": "Jmg0095", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reworded sentence to match what the (original/already there) source actually said.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anna_Francisca_de_Bruyns"}
{"title_page": "Priyamvada Kant", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox actor\n|name    = Priyamvada Kant\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1990|01|01}}\n| birth_place        = [[Delhi|India]]\n|occupation= Actress, Dancer\n|nationality= {{IND}}\n| known_for = [[Tenali Rama (TV series)]], [[Heropanti |Heropanti (2014)]]\n}}\n\n'''Priyamvada Kant''' is an [[India]]n actress and dancer and the winner of [[MTV Splitsvilla]] Season 12 where she was the ideal match of [[Shrey Mittal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyamvada Kant in The Buddy Project!|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/Priyamvada-Kant-in-The-Buddy-Project/articleshow/22120381.cms|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Priyamvada Kant opens a dance academy|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/Priyamvada-Kant-opens-a-dance-academy/articleshow/20628218.cms|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Priyamvada Kant turns businesswoman|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-priyamvada-kant-turns-businesswoman-4296958-NOR.html|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Talent, grit and freedom|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/05/18/stories/2007051852050200.htm|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref> She is popularly known for her role as Sharda in the Sab TV serial ''Tenali Rama''.\n\n==Career==\nIn August 2013, Kant joined the cast of Channel V's ''[[The Buddy Project]]'', playing the cameo role of Kamna.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bhopatkar|first=Tejashree|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news/Priyamvada-Kant-to-do-a-cameo-in-Channel-Vs-The-Buddy-Project-/articleshow/22120381.cms?| publisher=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|title=Priyamvada Kant in The Buddy Project!|accessdate=August 28, 2013|date=November 3, 2014}}</ref> In October 2014, she was cast as a replacement of Nisha Nagpal on [[Star Plus]]'s ''[[Ek Veer Ki Ardaas...Veera]]''.\n\nShe played the role of Kanika Jamwal in the show ''[[Swim Team (TV series)|Swim Team]]'' which aired on [[Channel V India]]. She also appeared in an episode of [[And TV]]'s ''Tujhse Naaraz Nahin Zindagi''. Priyamvada Kant is also a script writer. Her script was developed to the Zee TV serial - Sethji.\n\nKant is currently running a dance academy called Dancamaze.<ref name=\"Priyamvada Kant opens a dance academy\">{{cite web| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/Priyamvada-Kant-opens-a-dance-academy/articleshow/20628218.cms |title= Priyamvada Kant opens a dance academy|accessdate=2014-08-18}}</ref> Priyamvada Kant won MTV Splitsvilla Season 12 along with Shrey Mittal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rdduentertainment.com/shrey-mittal-and-priyamvada-kant-won-mtv-splitsvilla-12/|title=Shrey Mittal and Priyamvada Kant won [[MTV Splitsvilla]] 12|last=|first=|date=2020-01-17|website=RDDU ENTERTAINMENT|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n* [[Heropanti]] (2014), special appearance\n* [[Sooryavanshi (2020 film)|Sooryavanshi]] (2020), special appearance\n* [[Laxmmi Bomb]] (2020), cast as sundari lal\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show !! Channel !! Character\n|-\n| 2012 ||''[[Sasural Simar Ka]]''||[[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]]|| Anisha\n|-\n| 2013 ||''[[The Buddy Project]]''||[[Channel V India]]|| Kamna\n|-\n| 2014 ||''[[Love by Chance (Indian TV series)|Love by Chance]]''||[[Bindass]]|| Mishti\n|-\n| 2014 ||''[[Ek Veer Ki Ardaas...Veera]]''||[[Star Plus]]|| Simran\n|-\n| 2014 ||''[[Ek Rishta Aisa Bhi]]''||[[Sony Pal]]|| Samaira\n|-\n| 2015 ||''[[Tujhse Naaraaz Nahin Zindagi]]''||[[& TV]]|| Arunima Sinha (based on real life events)\n|-\n| 2015 ||''[[Swim Team (TV series)|Swim Team]]''||[[Channel V India]]|| Kanika Jamwal\n|-\n| 2015 ||''[[Pyaar Tune Kya Kiya (TV series)|Pyaar Tune Kya Kiya]]''||[[Zing (TV channel)|Zing]]|| Aditi\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017 ||''[[Sa