{"title_page": "2020\u201321 Tulane Green Wave men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n|CoachRank=\n|APRank=\n|mode=Basketball\n|year=2020\u201321\n|prev_year=2019\u201320\n|next_year=2021\u201322\n|team=Tulane Green Wave\n|image=Tulane Green Wave wordmark.svg\n|image_size=200\n|conference=American Athletic Conference\n|division=\n|short_conf=AAC\n|record=\n|conf_record=\n|head_coach=[[Ron Hunter]]\n|hc_year=2nd\n|asst_coach1=[[Ray McCallum]]\n|asst_coach2=Claude Pardue\n|asst_coach3=Kevin Johnson\n|stadium=[[Devlin Fieldhouse]]\n|champion=\n}}\n{{2020\u201321 American Athletic Conference men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2020\u201321 Tulane Green Wave men's basketball team''' represents [[Tulane University]] during the [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Green Wave, led by second-year head coach [[Ron Hunter]], play their home games at [[Devlin Fieldhouse]] in [[New Orleans|New Orleans, Louisiana]] as seventh-year members of the [[American Athletic Conference]].\n\n== Previous season ==\nThe [[2019\u201320 Tulane Green Wave men's basketball team|Green Wave]] 12\u201318, 4\u201314 in [[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] to finish in 12th place. They entered as the No. 12 seed in the [[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], which was ultimately cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for departure\n|-\n| K. J. Lawson || 1 || G/F || 6'7\" || 215 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis, TN]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Ray Ona Embo || 3 || G || 6'5\" || 195 || {{sort|3.5|RS Junior}} || [[Lognes|Lognes, France]] || Left team (mid-season)<ref>{{cit