 [[New Orleans|New Orleans, Louisiana]] as seventh-year members of the [[American Athletic Conference]].\n\n== Previous season ==\nThe [[2019\u201320 Tulane Green Wave men's basketball team|Green Wave]] 12\u201318, 4\u201314 in [[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] to finish in 12th place. They entered as the No. 12 seed in the [[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], which was ultimately cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for departure\n|-\n| K. J. Lawson || 1 || G/F || 6'7\" || 215 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis, TN]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Ray Ona Embo || 3 || G || 6'5\" || 195 || {{sort|3.5|RS Junior}} || [[Lognes|Lognes, France]] || Left team (mid-season)<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Smith|first=Guerry|author-link= |user=Guersmith\n |number=1201262657808093186 |date=9 Dec 2019 |title=#Tulane guard Ray Ona Embo has left the team and returned to France, coach Ron Hunter said after Sunday's win over Southern. Backing up Jordan Walker, Ona Embo was averaging 5.5 points, 2.5 rebounds, 1.3 assists and 21.8 minutes.|link=https://twitter.com/guersmith/status/1201262657808093186 |access-date=14 Apr 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Nic Thomas || 14 || G || 6'1\" || 185 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Arlington, Texas|Arlington, TX]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Christion Thompson || 25 || G || 6'4\" || 215 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Gonzales, Louisiana|Gonzales, LA]] || Graduated\n|}\n\n===Incoming Transfers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous School\n|-\n| Ryan Murphy || G || 6'2\" || 185 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Calabasas, California|Calabas