{"title_page": "Red Bull", "text_new": "{{short description|Energy drink sold by iranian company Red Bull GmbH}}\n{{about|the energy drink|the company|Red Bull GmbH|other uses|Red Bull (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{infobox beverage\n|logo         = RedBullEnergyDrink.svg\n|type         = [[Energy drink]]\n|proof        =\n|distributor  = [[Red Bull GmbH]]\n|origin       = [[Austria]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Who makes Red Bull? Red Bull Company - Origin & founder :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull USA |url=https://energydrink-us.redbull.com/en/company |website=energydrink-us.redbull.com |access-date=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n|introduced   = 1987\n|color       = Amber\n|ingredients = [[Caffeine]], [[taurine]],<ref>https://escholarship.org/content/qt65k8r3bd/qt65k8r3bd.pdf</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://escholarship.org/uc/item/65k8r3bd|title=Debunking the Effects of Taurine in Red Bull Energy Drink|first=Woojae|last=Kim|date=18 March 2003|journal=Nutrition Bytes|volume=9|issue=1|accessdate=18 March 2020|via=escholarship.org}}</ref> [[glucuronolactone]],<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A taurine and caffeine-containing drink stimulates cognitive performance and well-being|first1=R.|last1=Seidl|first2=A.|last2=Peyrl|first3=R.|last3=Nicham|first4=E.|last4=Hauser|date=18 March 2000|journal=Amino Acids|volume=19|issue=3\u20134|pages=635\u2013642|doi=10.1007/s007260070013|pmid=11140366}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Energy drink ingredients. Contribution of caffeine and taurine to performance outcomes|first1=Amy|last1=Peacock|first2=Frances Heritage|last2=Martin|first3=Andrea|last3=Carr|date=1 May 2013|journal=Appetite|volume=64|pages=1\u20134|doi=10.1016/j.appet.2012.12.021|pmid=23313701}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Taurine, caffeine, and energy drinks: Reviewing the risks to the adolescent brain|first1=Christine Perdan|last1=Curran|first2=Cecile A.|last2=Marczinski|date=1 December 2017|journal=Birth Defects Research|volume=109|issue=20|pages=1640\u20131648|doi=10.1002/bdr2.1177|pmid=29251842|pmc=5737830}}</ref> [[sucrose]] and [[glucose]], [[B vitamins|B-group vitamins]], and [[Spring (hydrology)|alpine spring water]]\n|variants     = [[#Flavours|Over 20]]\n|related      = [[Krating Daeng]], [[Red Bull Simply Cola|Red Bull Cola]], Red Bull Energy Shot, Red Bull Sugar-Free, Red Bull Total Zero\n|website      = {{URL|redbull.com}}\n}}\n'''Red Bull''' is an [[energy drink]] sold by [[Red Bull GmbH]], an Austrian company created in 1987. Red Bull has the highest market share of any energy drink in the world, with 6.790&nbsp;billion cans sold in a year ({{As of|2018|lc=y}}).<ref name=\"CompanyWebsite\">{{cite web|title=Who makes Red Bull|url=http://energydrink-us.redbull.com/company|first=Adam|last=Boome|date=31 May 2011|website=|access-date=30 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304204033/http://energydrink-us.redbull.com/company|archive-date=4 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Energy Drinks Build Their Buzz|url=http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/jan2005/sb2005015_8196_sb017.htm|work=BloombergBusinessweek|publisher=BLOOMBERG L.P|access-date=2012-08-19|author=Burt Helm|date=4 January 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Company Figures|url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/company-figures/001242939605518?pcs_c=PCS_Product&pcs_cid=1242937556133|work=Red Bull|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2012-08-19|author=Red Bull|year=2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://energydrink.redbull.com/company |title=Red Bull the company \u2013 Who makes Red Bull? Red Bull Origin :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull |publisher=Energydrink.redbull.com |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref>\n\nAustrian entrepreneur [[Dietrich Mateschitz]] was inspired by an existing energy drink named [[Krating Daeng]], which was first introduced and sold in [[Thailand]] by [[Chaleo Yoovidhya]]. He took this idea, modified the ingredients to suit the tastes of Westerners,<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VrO3O0h6I0wC |title=Asian Brand Strategy: How Asia Builds Strong Brands |last1=Roll |first1=Martin |isbn=9780230513068 |page=199 |publisher=Springer |date=17 October 2005 |access-date=2012-09-24}}</ref> and, in partnership with Chaleo, founded Red Bull&nbsp;GmbH in 1987 in Chakkapong, Thailand. In [[Thai language|Thai]], ''daeng'' means red, and a ''[[gaur|krating]]'' (known in English as a gaur or Indian bison) is a large species of wild [[bovine]] native to South Asia. Yoovidhya's heirs own majority stakes in both brands, and they both use the same red bull on yellow sun logo while continuing to market the separate drinks to the respective Thai and Western markets.\n\nRed Bull is sold in a tall and slim blue-silver can.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former F1 Driver David Coulthard Thrilled Shoppers Along Bukit Bintang in Red Bull Racings Show Car Run|url=http://www.cheryl-tay.com/news/former-f1-driver-david-coulthard-thrilled-shoppers-along-bukit-bintang-in-red-bull-racings-show-car-run.html|work=Va Va Vroom|publisher=Cheryl Tay Pte Ltd.|access-date=2012-07-27|author=Cheryl Tay|date=8 April 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108082847/http://cheryl-tay.com/news/former-f1-driver-david-coulthard-thrilled-shoppers-along-bukit-bintang-in-red-bull-racings-show-car-run.html|archive-date=8 January 2012}}</ref> Originally only available in a single nondescript flavor and regular or [[Diet soda|sugar-free formulas]], a line of \"color editions\" with artificial fruit flavors were added to the line beginning in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/chicago/news/2013/02/28/red-bull-ready-to-introduce-new-flavors.html|title=Red Bull introduces new flavors|first=Lewis|last=Lazare|work=American CIty Business Journals|date=28 February 2013|access-date=6 May 2018}}</ref> The Red Bull company slogan is \"Red Bull gives you wings\",<ref name=\"company\">{{cite web|url=http://authoring.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Products/Company-021242755317296|title=Company|work=Red Bull|access-date=2011-04-02|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130201063750/http://authoring.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Products/Company-021242755317296|archive-date=1 February 2013}}</ref> occasionally \"No Red Bull, no wings\". Rather than following a traditional approach to mass marketing, Red Bull has generated awareness and created a 'brand myth'<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kuehlwein|first1= JP|last2 =Chaefer|first2= Wolf|title=How modern prestige brands create meaning through mission and myth|journal=Journal of Brand Strategy|volume=5|issue=4|date= Spring 2017}}{{ISSN|2045-855X}}</ref><ref>Kuehlwein, JP. [https://masstoclass.wordpress.com/2015/12/15/ueber-brands-and-the-art-of-myth-making/ Ueber-Brands and The Art of Myth-Making]. www.ueberbrands.com 12/2015</ref> through proprietary extreme sport event series such as [[Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series]], [[Red Bull Air Race]], [[Crashed Ice|Red Bull Crashed Ice]] and stand-out stunts such as the [[Red Bull Stratos|Stratos space diving project]].<ref>Schaefer, Wolf and Kuehlwein, JP. 2015. Rethinking Prestige Branding \u2013 Secrets of the Ueber-Brands. Kogan Page. pp.77ff. {{ISBN|9780749470036}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull's marketing also includes multiple sports team ownerships ([[Formula One]] teams [[Red Bull Racing]] and [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]], [[Association football|football]] clubs [[RB Leipzig]], [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]], [[FC Liefering]], [[Red Bull Brasil]] and [[New York Red Bulls]]), celebrity endorsements, and music, through its record label [[Red Bull Records]].<ref name=\"Pump the Music\">{{Cite news|title=Pump the Music: Red Bull Eyes Starting Branded Music Label&nbsp;\u2014 NYPost.com|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/item_SY9XQMYwCgtsf6cCoINAOO;jsessionid=A41FF58821B638E4FD7E126596BCABFB|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130130130346/http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/item_SY9XQMYwCgtsf6cCoINAOO;jsessionid=A41FF58821B638E4FD7E126596BCABFB|url-status=dead|archive-date=30 January 2013|work=New York Post|first=Peter|last=Lauria|date=1 April 2008}}101013 NYPost.com</ref>\n\nEnergy drinks have been associated with health risks, such as masking the effects of [[Alcohol intoxication|intoxication]] when consumed with alcohol,<ref name=\"AFP2011\">{{Cite web|title = Combining energy drinks and alcohol|vauthors=Pennay A, Lubman DI, Miller P |date = 2011|access-date = 2015-08-12|url = http://www.racgp.org.au/download/documents/AFP/2011/March/201103pennay.pdf}}</ref> and excessive or repeated consumption can lead to cardiac and psychiatric conditions.<ref name=\"pmid25818530\"/><ref name=\"pmid25622514\"/> However, the [[European Food Safety Authority|European Food Safety Authority (EFSA)]] concluded that an adequate consumption of Red Bull and other popular energy drinks is safe and that the amount of caffeine in a standard Red Bull can is unlikely to interact adversely with other typical constituents of energy drinks or with alcohol.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Scientific Opinion on the safety of caffeine {{!}} Europ\u00e4ische Beh\u00f6rde f\u00fcr Lebensmittelsicherheit|url = http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/efsajournal/pub/4102|website = www.efsa.europa.eu|access-date = 2016-01-02|date = 2015-05-27}}</ref> Energy drinks have the effects that caffeine and sugar give, but there is no distinct evidence that the wide variety of other ingredients has any effect.<ref name=\"pmid23206286\"/>\n\n==History==\n\n[[File:Red Bull near Potala Palace.jpg|thumb|In front of the [[Potala Palace]], Tibet: a model of Red Bull in Chinese version is displayed.]]\n[[File:Red Bull Car in Israel (1).jpg|thumb|Red Bull car]]\n\nIn 1976, [[Chaleo Yoovidhya]] introduced a drink called [[Krating Daeng]] in Thailand, which means \"red [[gaur]]\" in English. It was popular among Thai truck drivers and labourers. While working for German manufacturer Blendax (later acquired by [[Procter & Gamble]]) in 1982, [[Dietrich Mateschitz]] travelled to Thailand and met Chaleo, owner of T.C. Pharmaceutical. During his visit, Mateschitz discovered that Krating Daeng helped cure his [[jet lag]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/people/displayStory.cfm?story_id=1120373 |title=Face value &#124; Selling energy |publisher=Economist.com |date=9 May 2002 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref> In 1984, Mateschitz co-founded [[Red Bull GmbH]] with Yoovidhya and turned it into an international brand. Each partner invested US$500,000 of savings to found the company. Yoovidhya and Mateschitz each held a 49 percent share of the new company. They gave the remaining two percent to Yoovidhya's son, Chalerm, but it was agreed that Mateschitz would run the company.<ref name=\"forbes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2005/0328/028_print.html|title=The Soda With Buzz|date=28 March 2005|author=Kerry A. Dolan|work=Forbes|access-date=20 June 2015}}</ref> The product was launched in Austria in 1987.\n\nIn Thailand, energy drinks are most popular with blue-collar workers. Red Bull re-positioned the drink as a trendy, upscale drink, first introducing it at Austrian ski resorts. Pricing was a key differentiator, with Red Bull positioned as a premium drink and Krating Daeng as a lower cost item. In many countries, both drinks are available, dominating both ends of the price spectrum.<ref name=BP-20151228 />\n\nIn 1992, the product expanded to [[Hungary]] and [[Slovenia]].<ref name=\"funding universe history\">{{cite web| title = Red Bull GmbH Company History | url = http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/Red-Bull-GmbH-Company-History.html | publisher = Funding Universe | access-date = 2007-10-12}}</ref> It entered Germany and the UK in 1994,<ref name=\"funding universe history\"/> the United States (via California) in 1997<ref name=\"funding universe history\"/> and the Middle East in 2000.<ref>{{Cite news| author = Ligaya, Armina | title = Region abuzz over energy drinks | work = [[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]] | date = 12 May 2010 | page = Business section, pp. 1, 6 | url = http://www.thenational.ae/business/retail/region-abuzz-over-energy-drinks | access-date = 2010-05-13}}</ref> In 2008, ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine listed both Chaleo and Mateschitz as the 250th&nbsp;richest people in the world with an estimated net worth of US$4&nbsp;billion.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_The-Worlds-Billionaires_CountryOfPrmRes_23.html |title=The World's Billionaires |magazine=Forbes.com |date=11 February 2008 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_The-Worlds-Billionaires_CountryOfPrmRes.html |title=The World's Billionaires |magazine=Forbes.com |date=11 February 2008 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull GmbH is headquartered in [[Fuschl am See]], an Austrian village of about 1,500 inhabitants near [[Salzburg]]. The company is 51 percent controlled by the Yoovidhya family who, for technical reasons, own the trademark in Europe and the US.<ref name=BP-20151228>{{cite news|last1=Nivatpumin|first1=Chiratas|last2=Treeraponpichit|first2=Busrin|title=Red Bull still charging ahead |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/business/news/808868/red-bull-still-charging-ahead|access-date=30 December 2015|work=Bangkok Post|date=28 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 1995, [[Krating Daeng]] authorized its drink, labelled as Red Bull, to be sold in [[People's Republic of China|China]]. Since 2014, the Austrian Red Bull (carbonated) has also been exported to China. This has created confusion since both drinks use the same brand name, in both English and Chinese.\n\nSimilarly, in Southeast Asia, Red Bull and Krating Daeng are often confused as both use the Red Bull name in their packaging, although they are two separate products aimed at different markets. The main difference is that Red Bull comes in a tall blue and silver can while the [[Thailand]] Red Bull, or Krating Daeng, is in a smaller gold can. The two drinks also differ in terms of taste\u2014Red Bull has less sugar and is carbonated. The flavouring used for Red Bull is still produced in Bangkok and exported worldwide.<ref name=BP-20151228 />\n\n==Ingredients==\n{{replace|{{Infobox nutritional value\n| name            = \n| image           = <!-- Filename is enough -->\n| image_size      = <!-- Defaults to 235px -->\n| image_alt       = \n| caption         = \n| serving_size    = 100 mL<ref name=\"can photo\">{{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/bM8Yl2Ar.jpg|title=Enerji \u0130\u00e7ece\u011fi|format=photography of part of the can with nutrition information, BiH import|lang=tr|date=16 September 2019|accessdate=16 September 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916100514/https://i.imgur.com/bM8Yl2Ar.jpg|archivedate=16 September 2019}}</ref>\n| kJ              = 205\n| carbs           = 11.3\n| starch          = \n| sugars          = 11.3\n| lactose         = \n| fiber           = <!-- or |fibre= -->\n| fat             = 0\n| satfat          = 0\n| transfat        = \n| monofat         = \n| polyfat         = \n| omega3fat       = \n| omega6fat       = \n| protein         = 0\n| tryptophan      = \n| threonine       = \n| isoleucine      = \n| leucine         = \n| lysine          = \n| methionine      = \n| cystine         = \n| phenylalanine   = \n| tyrosine        = \n| valine          = \n| arginine        = \n| histidine       = \n| alanine         = \n| aspartic acid   = \n| glutamic acid   = \n| glycine         = \n| proline         = \n| serine          = \n| hydroxyproline  = \n| water           = \n| cholesterol     = \n| alcohol         = \n| caffeine        = \n| vitA_ug         = \n| vitA_iu         = \n| betacarotene_ug = \n| lutein_ug       = \n| thiamin_mg      = \n| riboflavin_mg   = \n| niacin_mg       = 8.0\n| pantothenic_mg  = 2.0\n| vitB6_mg        = 2.0\n| folate_ug       = \n| vitB12_ug       = 2.0\n| choline_mg      = \n| vitC_mg         = \n| vitD_ug         = \n| vitD_iu         = \n| vitE_mg         = \n| vitK_ug         = \n| calcium_mg      = \n| copper_mg       = \n| iron_mg         = \n| magnesium_mg    = \n| manganese_mg    = \n| phosphorus_mg   = \n| potassium_mg    = \n| selenium_ug     =\n| sodium_mg       = \n| zinc_mg         = \n| opt1n           = [[Salt]]s\n| opt1v           = 0.205 g\n| opt2n           = [[Taurine]]\n| opt2v           = 80 mg\n| opt3n           = [[Caffeine]]\n| opt3v           = 15 mg\n| opt4n           = \n| opt4v           = \n| note            = \n| source          = \n| source_usda     = \n| noRDA           = \n| float           = right\n}}|Nutritional value|{{abbr|Nutritional value|Red&thinsp;Bull Energy Drink, Enerji \u0130\u00e7ece\u011fi [Turkish production]}}}}\n\nDepending on the country, Red Bull contains different amounts of [[caffeine]], [[taurine]], [[B vitamins]] (B3, B5, B6, B12) and simple sugars ([[sucrose]] and [[glucose]]) in a [[buffer solution]] of [[carbonated water]], [[sodium bicarbonate|baking soda]] and [[magnesium carbonate]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Red Bull Ingredients :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull |url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/Red-Bull-Energy-Drink/001242937921959?pcs_c=PCS_Product&pcs_cid=1242937842064&pcs_pvt=ingredient|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2012-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.caffeineinformer.com/caffeine-content/red-bull|title=Caffeine in Red Bull|website=www.caffeineinformer.com|access-date=2017-12-29}}</ref> To produce Red Bull Sugarfree, sugars sucrose and glucose have been replaced by the sweeteners [[acesulfame K]] and [[aspartame]]/[[sucralose]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/Red-Bull-Sugarfree/001242937921959?pcs_cid=1242937877523&pcs_pvt=ingredient&pcs_iid=1243128878373 |title=Sweeteners in Red Bull zero sugar? :: Energy drink sugar free |publisher=Red Bull |access-date=2012-09-24}}</ref> \n\nPrevious formulations of Red Bull contained 0.24% [[glucuronolactone]] (600 mg of glucuronolactone in a 250 ml can),<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Alford|first=C.|last2=Cox|first2=H.|last3=Wescott|first3=R.|date=2001|title=The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood|journal=Amino Acids|volume=21|issue=2|pages=139\u2013150|issn=0939-4451|pmid=11665810|doi=10.1007/s007260170021}}</ref> but this ingredient was removed.\n\n==Flavours==\nRed Bull identifies its flavours as \"editions\".\n\n===Current===\n*Original (amber)\n*Sugar-free (5 calories)\n*Total Zero (no calories)\n*Red (cranberry)\n*Ruby/Red (grapefruit)\n*Blue (blueberry)\n*Yellow/Tropical (tropical fruit/mango papaya)\n*Orange/Mandarin (mandarin/orange/orange-[[kumquat]])\n*Green/Kiwi (kiwi-apple)\n*White/Coconut (coconut berry)\n*Peach (peach-nectarine)\n*Pear Sugar-Free (pear)\n*Lime Sugar-Free (lime)\n*Purple/Acai Sugar-Free (a\u00e7ai)\n*Purple/Acai (acai berry)\n*Lime (lime-lemon)\n*Orange Sugar-free (orange) \n*Yellow/Tropical Sugar-free (tropical)\n*Winter (plum twist)\n*Summer Edition Beach Breeze (2019) (azure can, coconut/tutti-frutti)\n\n===Discontinued===\n*Silver (dry lime)\n*Spring Edition (sakura cherry)\n*Orange Total Zero (orange)\n*Cherry Total Zero (wild cherry)\n*Blue Edition (grape)\n\nSeveral of these flavors have been rebranded for special events (the special grapefruit flavor, for example, has been branded as the \"Bull\" Edition, the \"Red Italian\" Edition, and the \"[[Formula 1|F1]] Edition\").\n\n==Health effects==\n{{further|Energy drinks#Effects}}\nClaims about the drink's effects and performance have been challenged on various occasions, with the UK's [[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] imposing advertising restrictions in 2001 in response to complaints recorded as early as 1997.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/1133348.stm |title=HEALTH &#124; Energy drink claims rejected |work=BBC News |date=24 January 2001 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref>\n\nEnergy drinks have the effects that caffeine and sugar provide, but experts still argue about the possible effects of the other [[ingredients]].<ref name=\"pmid23206286\">{{cite journal | vauthors = McLellan TM, Lieberman HR | title = Do energy drinks contain active components other than caffeine? | journal = Nutrition Reviews | volume = 70 | issue = 12 | pages = 730\u201344 | date = December 2012 | pmid = 23206286 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1111/j.1753-4887.2012.00525.x }}</ref> Most of the effects of energy drinks on cognitive performance, such as increased attention and reaction speed, are primarily due to the presence of caffeine.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite journal | vauthors = van den Eynde F, van Baelen PC, Portzky M, Audenaert K | title = [The effects of energy drinks on cognitive performance] | journal = Tijdschrift voor Psychiatrie | volume = 50 | issue = 5 | pages = 273\u201381 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18470842 }}</ref> There is evidence that energy drinks can increase mental<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Alford C, Cox H, Wescott R | title = The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 21 | issue = 2 | pages = 139\u201350 | date = 1 January 2001 | pmid = 11665810 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170021 | url = http://eprints.uwe.ac.uk/96/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Tijdschrift voor Psychiatrie - Author index: Baelen, P.C. van |url=http://www.tijdschriftvoorpsychiatrie.nl/en/zoeken/artikel.php?autid=2007&pgr=0 |date=21 December 2008 |access-date=2016-02-02 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081221221448/http://www.tijdschriftvoorpsychiatrie.nl/en/zoeken/artikel.php?autid=2007&pgr=0 |archive-date=21 December 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mets MA, Ketzer S, Blom C, van Gerven MH, van Willigenburg GM, Olivier B, Verster JC | title = Positive effects of Red Bull\u00ae Energy Drink on driving performance during prolonged driving | journal = Psychopharmacology | volume = 214 | issue = 3 | pages = 737\u201345 | date = April 2011 | pmid = 21063868 | pmc = 3053448 | doi = 10.1007/s00213-010-2078-2 }}</ref> and athletic<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Baum M, Weiss M | title = The influence of a taurine containing drink on cardiac parameters before and after exercise measured by echocardiography | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 20 | issue = 1 | pages = 75\u201382 | date = 1 January 2001 | pmid = 11310932 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170067 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Gei\u00df KR, Jester I, Falke W, Hamm M, Waag KL | title = The effect of a taurine-containing drink on performance in 10 endurance-athletes | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 7 | issue = 1 | pages = 45\u201356 | date = February 1994 | pmid = 24185972 | doi = 10.1007/BF00808445 }}</ref> performance. Performance during prolonged driving is increased after consumption of Red Bull.<ref name=\":1\" /> Other tests for physical performance showed results such as increased endurance and power. Red Bull energy drink increased upper body muscle endurance during repeated Wingate tests in young healthy adults.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Forbes SC, Candow DG, Little JP, Magnus C, Chilibeck PD | title = Effect of Red Bull energy drink on repeated Wingate cycle performance and bench-press muscle endurance | journal = International Journal of Sport Nutrition and Exercise Metabolism | volume = 17 | issue = 5 | pages = 433\u201344 | date = October 2007 | pmid = 18046053 | doi = 10.1123/ijsnem.17.5.433 }}</ref> Excessive or repeated consumption of energy drinks can lead to cardiac and psychiatric conditions.<ref name=\"pmid25818530\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sanchis-Gomar F, Pareja-Galeano H, Cervellin G, Lippi G, Earnest CP | title = Energy drink overconsumption in adolescents: implications for arrhythmias and other cardiovascular events | journal = The Canadian Journal of Cardiology | volume = 31 | issue = 5 | pages = 572\u20135 | date = May 2015 | pmid = 25818530 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/j.cjca.2014.12.019 | hdl = 11268/3906 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid25622514\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Petit A, Karila L, Lejoyeux M | title = [Abuse of energy drinks: does it pose a risk?] | journal = Presse M\u00e9dicale | volume = 44 | issue = 3 | pages = 261\u201370 | date = March 2015 | pmid = 25622514 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/j.lpm.2014.07.029 }}</ref>\n\nThe [[European Food Safety Authority]] (EFSA) concluded that exposure to taurine and glucuronolactone at the levels presently used in energy drinks is not a safety concern.<ref name=EFSA935>{{cite journal |url=http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/efsajournal/pub/935 |title=The use of taurine and D-glucurono-\u03b3-lactone as constituents of the so-called 'energy' drinks |journal=The EFSA Journal |year=2009 |volume=935 |issue=2 |pages=1\u201331 |author=EFSA Panel on Food Additives and Nutrient Sources added to Food |doi=10.2903/j.efsa.2009.935|doi-access=free }}</ref> In a separate analysis, they also concluded that there is insufficient evidence to support a number of commercial health claims about taurine.<ref name=EFSA2009>Scientific Opinion on the substantiation of health claims related to taurine and protection of DNA, proteins and lipids from oxidative damage (ID 612,1658, 1959), energy-yielding metabolism (ID 614), and delay in the onset of fatigue and enhancement of physical performance (ID 1660) pursuant to Article 13(1) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, European Food Safety Authority 2009, https://efsa.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.2903/j.efsa.2009.1260</ref> A review published in 2008 found no documented reports of negative or positive health effects associated with the amount of [[taurine]] used in energy drinks, including Red Bull. The review also states that though the caffeine and sugar levels in the energy drink are comparable to those present in coffee and fruit juice respectively, these levels have been shown to cause adverse health effects.<ref name=McQueen>{{cite journal | vauthors = Clauson KA, Shields KM, McQueen CE, Persad N | title = Safety issues associated with commercially available energy drinks | journal = Journal of the American Pharmacists Association | volume = 48 | issue = 3 | pages = e55\u201363; quiz e64\u20137 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18595815 | doi = 10.1331/JAPhA.2008.07055 }}</ref>\n \nIn its scientific opinion on the safety of caffeine of 2015, the EFSA concluded that \"consumption of other constituents of [[energy drinks]] at concentrations commonly present in such beverages would not affect the safety of single doses of caffeine up to 200 mg.\" Also, the consumption of alcohol, leading to a blood alcohol content of about 0.08%, would, according to the EFSA, not affect the safety of single doses of caffeine up to 200&nbsp;mg. Up to these levels of intake, caffeine is unlikely to mask the subjective perception of alcohol intoxication. Habitual use of caffeine up to 400&nbsp;mg per day does not.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAccording to [[SAMHSA]], \"the number of emergency department (ED) visits\" among people over age 12 related to energy drinks doubled between 2007 and 2011 in the US (from 10,068 to 20,783).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/spot124-energy-drinks-2014.pdf |title=1 in 10 Energy Drink-Related Emergency Department Visits Results in Hospitalization |publisher=Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration |access-date=9 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Caffeine content===\nThe [[caffeine]] content of a single can of Red Bull is approximately 80\u201340&nbsp;mg{{\\}}250&nbsp;mL (32\u201315&nbsp;mg{{\\}}100&nbsp;mL).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://coffeetea.about.com/od/caffeine/gr/redbull.htm |title=Red Bull caffeine beverage review |publisher=[[About.com]] |date=22 October 2009 |access-date=2012-05-29 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415002317/http://coffeetea.about.com/od/caffeine/gr/redbull.htm |archive-date=15 April 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/beverages/7399/2 |title=Nutrition Facts and Analysis for Energy drink, RED BULL, with added caffeine, niacin, pantothenic acid, vitamins B6 and B12 |publisher=Cond\u00e9 Nast |access-date=2012-05-29}}</ref><ref name=\"can photo\"/> This is about the same as one i.e. half a cup of coffee, or slightly less or more depending on the brewing method and country of production.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://coffeefaq.com/site/node/22 |title=How much caffeine is there in [drink/food/pill]? |publisher=Coffeefaq.com |date=15 January 2006 |access-date=2012-09-24|first=Daniel |last=Owen}}{{self-published source|date=April 2013}}</ref>{{self-published inline|date=April 2013}} The caffeine level in Red Bull varies depending on country, as some countries have legal restrictions on how much caffeine is allowed in drinks. As is the case with other caffeinated beverages, Red Bull drinkers may experience [[Energy drink#Adverse effects|adverse effects]] as a result of overuse. Excessive consumption may induce mild to moderate [[euphoria (emotion)|euphoria]] primarily caused by stimulant properties of caffeine and may also induce agitation, [[anxiety (mood)|anxiety]], irritability and [[insomnia]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Alford C, Cox H, Wescott R | title = The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 21 | issue = 2 | pages = 139\u201350 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11665810 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Richards G, Smith AP | title = A Review of Energy Drinks and Mental Health, with a Focus on Stress, Anxiety, and Depression | journal = Journal of Caffeine Research | volume = 6 | issue = 2 | pages = 49\u201363 | date = June 2016 | pmid = 27274415 | pmc = 4892220 | doi = 10.1089/jcr.2015.0033 }}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nThe general population of healthy adults is not at risk for potential adverse effects from caffeine if they limit their consumption to 400&nbsp;mg per day, which is the equivalent of 5 standard cans, with one can being 250ml in volume.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/fn-an/securit/addit/caf/index-eng.php |title=It's Your Health \u2013 Caffeine |publisher=Health Canada |date=13 April 2012 |access-date=24 November 2014}}</ref> Consumption of a single energy drink will not lead to excessive caffeine intake.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Nawrot\">{{cite journal |doi=10.1192/apt.11.6.432 |name-list-format=vanc|title=Neuropsychiatric effects of caffeine |year=2005 |last1=Winston |first1=AP |journal=Advances in Psychiatric Treatment |volume=11 |issue=6 |pages=432\u2013439|doi-access=free }}</ref> Adverse effects associated with caffeine consumption in amounts greater than 400&nbsp;mg include nervousness, irritability, sleeplessness, increased urination, abnormal heart rhythms ([[Heart arrhythmia|arrhythmia]]), and [[dyspepsia]]. Consumption also has been known to cause [[pupil dilation]] when taken with certain antidepressants or [[SSRI]]s.<ref name=\"Nawrot\" /><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Jin MJ, Yoon CH, Ko HJ, Kim HM, Kim AS, Moon HN, Jung SP | title = The Relationship of Caffeine Intake with Depression, Anxiety, Stress, and Sleep in Korean Adolescents | journal = Korean Journal of Family Medicine | volume = 37 | issue = 2 | pages = 111\u20136 | date = March 2016 | pmid = 27073610 | pmc = 4826990 | doi = 10.4082/kjfm.2016.37.2.111 }}</ref> Caffeine dosage is not required to be on the product label for food in the United States, unlike drugs, but some advocates are urging the FDA to change this practice. (Red Bull voluntarily lists the caffeine content in each can along with the ingredient list.)<ref>[https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94973371 Warning: Energy Drinks Contain Caffeine] by Allison Aubrey. Morning Edition, National Public Radio, 24 September 2008.</ref>\n\n==Market approval and legal status==\nAuthorities in France, [[Denmark]], and [[Norway]] initially kept Red Bull from being sold domestically.<ref name=\"2004CourtRuling\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/health-news/European-court-backs-ban-on-red-bull-over-health-concerns-68019.html|title=European court backs ban on Red Bull over health concerns|date=7 February 2004|last=Frith|first=Maxine|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|access-date=2010-11-22|location=London}}</ref> However, {{as of|2014|lc=y}}, it is on sale in all 28 [[member states of the European Union]] and in more than 167 countries around the world.\n\nThe French food safety agency was concerned about [[taurine]]. A Red Bull drink that did not contain taurine was introduced. The French refusal of market approval was challenged by the European Commission, and partially upheld by the [[European Court of Justice]] in 2004.<ref name=\"2004CourtRuling\" /> The French food safety agency relented in 2008, because it was unable to prove a definite health risk, taurine-related or not.<ref name=\"FranceBanEnd\">{{Cite news|title=France ends 12-year ban on energy drink Red Bull|location=Paris|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=15 July 2008|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL1576964720080715|access-date=2010-11-22}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, the Kuwaiti [[Ministry of Commerce (Kuwait)|Ministry of Commerce]] banned Red Bull for people under 16 after it had allegedly caused heart attacks for a 16-year-old and a 21-year-old national squash team player.<ref>{{cite web | title = Kuwaiti player dies after taking energy drinks |publisher = GulfNews| url = http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/kuwait/kuwaiti-player-dies-after-taking-energy-drinks-1.1184369 |author=Habib Toumi, Bureau Chief|date=16 May 2013| access-date = 2014-07-05  }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = KUNA : Decisions regulating sale of energy drinks issued \u2013 Economics \u2013 21/10/2012 | url = http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2269729&language=en |date= 21 October 2012|access-date = 2014-07-05 |publisher=[[Kuwait News Agency]] (KUNA)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | script-title=ar:\u0643\u0648\u0646\u0627 : \u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u0627\u0631\u0627 \u064a\u0646\u0638\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u062a\u0627\u062c \u0648\u0639\u0631\u0636 \u0648\u0628\u064a\u0639 \u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0642\u0629 \u2013 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u2013 21 October 2012 | url = http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2269682&Language=ar | date= 21 October 2012|access-date = 2014-07-05 |publisher=[[Kuwait News Agency]] (KUNA)|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | script-title=ar:\"\u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629\": \u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0642\u0629 \u0645\u0645\u0646\u0648\u0639\u0629 \u0644\u0645\u0646 \u062f\u0648\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0640 16 | publisher=[[Al-Qabas newspaper]] | url=http://www.alqabas.com.kw/node/244222 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708011326/http://www.alqabas.com.kw/node/244222 | url-status=dead | archive-date=2014-07-08 | date=21 October 2012 | access-date=2014-07-05 | language=ar }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Red Bull and a crisis in Kuwait that hasn't hit the headlines |publisher= Alex of Arabia's Blog | url = http://alexofarabia.com/2013/04/20/red-bull-and-a-crisis-in-kuwait-that-hasnt-hit-the-headlines/ | access-date = 2014-07-05 |date= 2013-04-20 }}\n</ref><ref name=\"Red Bull Kuwait Loses Millions\">{{cite web|title=Red Bull Kuwait Loses Millions|url=http://www.q8critic.com/red-bull-kuwait-loses-millions|publisher=Q8Critic|date=24 October 2012|access-date=2013-06-28|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625023916/http://www.q8critic.com/red-bull-kuwait-loses-millions/|archive-date=25 June 2013}}</ref><ref>http://omarker.com/?p=15727{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Litigation==\nIn 2013, Red Bull told the Redwell Brewery, a [[Norfolk]] [[micro brewery]], to change its name or face legal action, because it sounded too similar to Red Bull. The eight-man brewery in [[Norwich]] was told its name could \"confuse\" customers and \"tarnish\" its trademark.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-norfolk-23697138 |title=Red Bull pursues Redwell brewery in Norwich over name |work=[[BBC News]] |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref> The two companies reached a settlement permitting Redwell to continue using its name.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-norfolk-23705255 |title=Red Bull ends dispute with Redwell brewery in Norwich |work=[[BBC News]] |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Red Bull faced a US$13&nbsp;million settlement addressing two consumer class action lawsuits in the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.law360.com/articles/563228/red-bull-puts-up-13m-to-settle-false-advertising-suit|title=Red Bull Puts Up $13M To Settle False Advertising Suit \u2013 Law360|website=www.law360.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> The listed plaintiffs were Benjamin Careathers, David Wolf, and Miguel Almarez<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://topclassactions.com/lawsuit-settlements/lawsuit-news/36145-red-bull-agrees-13m-false-advertising-class-action-settlement/|title=Red Bull Agrees to $13M False Advertising Class Action Settlement|date=4 August 2014|work=Top Class Actions|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> who sued the company for Red Bull's marketing and labeling, claiming that the company violated \"express warranty and unjust enrichment\" since their products were first launched by claiming performance-enhancing benefits from the drink's ingredients which were not substantiated by scientific studies.<ref name=bevnet>{{cite web|title=Red Bull to Pay $13 Million|url=http://www.bevnet.com/news/2014/red-bull-to-pay-13-million-for-false-advertising-settlement|website=bevnet.com|publisher=Law360.|access-date=2014-10-21|date=2014-08-05}}</ref> The court hearing took place the morning of 1 May 2015 in an attempt to determine approval for the settlement. Customers that submitted claims then have the opportunity to receive a US$10 cash reimbursement or product option of US$15 in Red Bull products<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/drink-red-bull-you-may-have-10-coming-to-you/ |title=Drink Red Bull? You may have $10 coming to you |publisher=cbsnews.com |date=9 October 2014 |access-date=2015-02-16}}</ref> within 150 days of the approved appeals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/29550003 |title=So Red Bull doesn't actually 'give you wings' |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=9 October 2014 |access-date=2014-11-03}}</ref>  Contrary to false reports from some [[news media|news outlets]], the lawsuit was not about the drink failing to give the consumer actual wings.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[Snopes]] |url=https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/red-bulls-wings/ |title=Fact check: Red Bull does (not) give you wings |last=O\u2019Reilly |first=Laura |date=8 October 2014 |access-date=10 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Advertising==\n[[File:Max_Verstappen_(36132602681).jpg|thumb|[[Max Verstappen]] in the [[Red Bull RB13]], the 2017 Formula One car of the [[Red Bull Racing]] Team]]\n[[File:Red Bull Cobra G\u00f3raszka 7.JPG|thumb|Red Bull's [[AH-1 Cobra|TAH-1F Cobra]] helicopter assembled by [[Chuck Aaron]], owned by the [[Flying Bulls]]]]\n[[File:North American B-25J Mitchell Red Bull (The Flying Bulls) N6123C (9292015992).jpg|thumb|right|A Red Bull [[North American B-25 Mitchell]]]]\nSince 1997, Red Bull has been making commercials bearing its slogan \"Red Bull gives you wings,\"<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/1133348.stm | title=Energy drink claims rejected| date=2001-01-24}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull's international marketing campaign targets young men mostly with [[extreme sports]]. These range from mountain biking,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mbaction.com/uncategorized/red-bull-rampage-recap|title=Red Bull Rampage Recap|last=sean|website=Mountain Bike Action Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08|date=2017-02-05}}</ref> BMX,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/photos/gallery/_/id/9362075/image/7/aj-anaya-red-bull-framed-reactions-bmx-park-competition-amsterdam|title=Drew Bezanson wins Red Bull Framed Reactions BMX Park comp|work=XGames|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> motocross,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://motocross.transworld.net/videos/2017-red-bull-ktm-team-intro/#K83xyH80VQMW3xvR.97|title=2017 Red Bull KTM {{!}} Team Intro {{!}} Transworld Motocross|date=18 December 2016|work=Transworld Motocross|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> windsurfing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pwaworldtour.com/index.php?id=35&tx_news_pi1%5Bnews%5D=3694&tx_news_pi1%5Bcontroller%5D=News&tx_news_pi1%5Baction%5D=detail&cHash=a6e5007e8e6cb2f3da520cf203fc4183|title=Red Bull Storm Chase|last=(PWA)|first=Professional Windsurfing Association|work=PWA World Tour|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> snowboarding,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.snowboarder.com/tag/red-bull-snowboarding/|title=Red Bull Snowboarding {{!}} Snowboarder Magazine.|website=Snowboarder Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> skateboarding,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skateboarding.transworld.net/tag/red-bull-skateboarding/|title=red bull skateboarding {{!}} TransWorld SKATEboarding|website=TransWorld SKATEboarding|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> kayaking,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/chasing-niagara-falls-in-a-kayak|title=Chasing Niagara Falls in a Kayak {{!}} VICE Sports|work=VICE Sports|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309072917/https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/chasing-niagara-falls-in-a-kayak|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> rowing,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/?job_id=4239|title=Red Bull High Stakes \u2013 Overview|website=www.regattacentral.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> wakeboarding,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wakeboardingmag.com/red-bull-wake-steel-2016|title=Red Bull Wake of Steel 2016|work=Wakeboarding Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> cliff-diving,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/red-bull-cliff-diving-world-202700299.html|title=Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series Announces 2017 Schedule|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309072250/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/red-bull-cliff-diving-world-202700299.html|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[parkour]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://greece.greekreporter.com/2016/10/02/bart-van-der-linden-wins-parkour-red-bull-art-of-motion-in-santorini-video/|title=...Wins Parkour Red Bull Art of Motion in Santorini (video) {{!}} GreekReporter.com|last=Kolasa-Sikiaridi|first=Kerry|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> surfing,<ref>{{Citation|title=RED BULL QIANTANG: SURFING SHOOTOUT|url=http://www.surfline.com/video/contests/red-bull-qiantang-surfing-shootout_95487|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> skating,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visitsaintpaul.com/things-to-do/winter-fun/red-bull-crashed-ice-championship/|title=Red Bull Crashed Ice Championship in Saint Paul, MN \u2013 Visit Saint Paul|website=www.visitsaintpaul.com|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309061655/http://www.visitsaintpaul.com/things-to-do/winter-fun/red-bull-crashed-ice-championship/|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> freestyle motocross,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://iq.intel.com/red-bull-x-fighters/|title=Real-Time Data Tech Dazzles Red Bull X-Fighters Fans|date=22 June 2016|work=iQ by Intel|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916210645/http://iq.intel.com/red-bull-x-fighters/|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> rallycross,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.racer.com/international/world-rally/item/138614-red-bull-global-rallycross-new-england-set-for-june|title=Red Bull Global Rallycross New England set for June|last=GRC|website=www.racer.com|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308145010/http://www.racer.com/international/world-rally/item/138614-red-bull-global-rallycross-new-england-set-for-june|archive-date=8 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Formula&nbsp;1 racing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/red-bull-positive-rb13-can-challenge-mercedes-in-f1-2017-879644/|title=Red Bull \"positive\" RB13 can challenge Mercedes in F1 2017|work=Motorsport.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> [[NASCAR]] racing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.archrival.com/work/29/red-bull-racing-in-nascar/|title=Archrival {{!}} Red Bull Racing in NASCAR|work=Archrival|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> to breakdancing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.axs.com/redbull-flying-bach-tour-brings-bach-and-breakdancing-to-dallas-in-201-106667|title=Redbull Flying Bach tour brings Bach and breakdancing to Dallas in 2017|work=AXS|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> Red Bull uses music and videogames, and has enlisted celebrities, such as [[Eminem]] (sponsoring the Red Bull \"EmSee Battle Rap championships\").<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/calling-battle-rappers-enter-red-bull-emsee-miami-and-win-a-trip-to-the-finals-in-atlanta-6462178|title=Calling Battle Rappers! Enter Red Bull EmSee Miami and Win a Trip to the Finals in Atlanta|last=Pajot|first=S.|date=3 November 2011|work=Miami New Times|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> It hosts events like art shows and the \"[[Red Bull Flugtag]]\" (German for \"flight day\" or \"flying day\").<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/life/2017/03/07/red-bulls-high-flying-flugtag-competition-return-nashville/98834598/|title=Red Bull's high-flying Flugtag competition to return to Nashville|work=The Tennessean|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull owns football teams, with clubs in Austria,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/austria/fc-red-bull-salzburg/165/|title=Austria \u2013 FC Salzburg \u2013 Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news \u2013 Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> Germany,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/12/16/rb-leipzigs-bundesliga-debut-is-like-a-fairy-tale-in-which-the-bad-guys-are-winning/|title=Analysis {{!}} RB Leipzig's Bundesliga debut is like a fairy tale in which the bad guys are winning|website=Washington Post|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> the United States,<ref name=\":2\" /> and Brazil<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/brazil/red-bull-brasil/14538/|title=Brazil \u2013 Red Bull Brasil \u2013 Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news \u2013 Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> featuring the Red Bull trademark in their names. By associating the drink's image with these activities, the company seeks to promote a \"cool\" public image and raise brand power. The energy drink has created a market for over 150 related types of products.<ref>{{cite web|title=RED BULL HISTORY|url=http://www.speedace.info/red_bull.htm|website=speedace.info|publisher=Electrick Publications.|access-date=2012-07-27}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[PlayStation 3]]'s social gaming platform, [[PlayStation Home]], Red Bull developed its own [[List of PlayStation Home Game Spaces#Non-gaming Company Spaces|in-game island]], specifically advertising its energy drink and the [[Red Bull Air Race]] event (for which the space is named) released in January 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/red-bull-becomes-first-brand-playstation-home/890098|title=Red Bull becomes first brand on PlayStation Home|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> In late November 2009, Red Bull produced two new spaces, the [[Red Bull Illume]] space, and the Red Bull Beach space featuring the [[Red Bull Flugtag]], both released on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kotaku.com/5443106/red-bull-gives-playstation-home-new-things-to-do/|title=Red Bull Gives PlayStation Home New Things To Do|last=Fahey|first=Mike|work=Kotaku|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704153417/https://kotaku.com/5443106/red-bull-gives-playstation-home-new-things-to-do/|archive-date=4 July 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In January 2012, Red Bull released its first personal space called the \"Red Bull House of Skate\" featuring an indoor skate park.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yourpshome.net/showcase/red-bull-house-of-skate.90/|title=Red Bull House of Skate|work=YourPSHome.net|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn the [[App Store (iOS)|Apple App store]] Red Bull also has a few apps which include: RedBull.com, [[Red Bull TV]], The Red Bulletin, RBMA Radio, Red Bull iFunk, Wings For Life- Selfie Run. As well as some games on the app store which are: Bike Unchained, Red Bull Kart Fighter 3, Red Bull Air Race The Game, Red Bull Racers.<ref>{{Cite web|title = iTunes \u2013 Browse the top free apps on the App Store \u2013 Apple|url = https://www.apple.com/itunes/charts/free-apps/|website = Apple|access-date = 2016-02-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, the company enlisted Adrian Newey to design a prototype racing car, the [[Red Bull X2010]], for the videogame ''[[Gran Turismo 5]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gtvault.com/gt5/setup-view/s_sid::9231/Gran-Turismo-Red-Bull-X2011-Prototype--11/|title=GTVault \u2013 Gran Turismo 5Setup for|website=www.gtvault.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\n===Red Bull House of Art===\nThe '''Red Bull House of Art''' is an art fellowship program that was launched by Red Bull.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Abbey-Lambertz|first1=Kate|title=Red Bull House of Art Bolsters Detroit Scene By Giving Artists on the Verge A Leg Up (VIDEO)|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/red-bull-house-of-art-detroit-cycle-5_n_3720077.html|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2015-01-24|date=7 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=freep>{{cite news|last1=Hammerstein|first1=BJ|title=Detroit artist star of new Red Bull ad|url=http://archive.freep.com/article/20140125/NEWS01/301250052/Detroit-made-Red-Bull-ad-to-air-during-Grammys|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|access-date=2015-01-24}}</ref> The program is held in multiple cities, most notably the Red Bull House of Art programs in Detroit, Michigan and [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]], and the program typically consists of a three-month period during which time six to eight participants will create new artwork with the intent to display it in a final exhibition.<ref name=TOB>{{cite web|last1=Rigby|first1=Claire|title=Red Bull Station opens up downtown|url=http://www.timeout.com.br/sao-paulo/en/art/features/458/red-bull-station-opens-up-downtown|publisher=Time Out Brazil|access-date=2015-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128131911/http://www.timeout.com.br/sao-paulo/en/art/features/458/red-bull-station-opens-up-downtown|archive-date=28 January 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=mt1>{{cite news|last1=DeVito|first1=Lee|title=Meet the creative minds behind the Red Bull House of Art's Cycle 8|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/detroit/meet-the-creative-minds-behind-the-red-bull-house-of-arts-cycle-8/Content?oid=2214656|newspaper=Metro Times|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref> During the fellowship the artists receive unlimited access to the galleries and a [[stipend]] for art supplies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Trevino|first1=Jessica J.|title=Meet the 6 local artists featured in the Red Bull House of Art exhibit|url=http://www.freep.com/article/20140806/ENT05/308060039/red-bull-house-exhibit-detroit|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe program has received criticism as being an \"elaborate advertising scheme\",<ref>{{cite web|last1=DeVito|first1=Lee|title=Red Bull House of Art|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/detroit/red-bull-house-of-art/Content?oid=2145533|publisher=MetroTimes|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref> as some of the artwork has been used in Red Bull advertising campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lacy|first1=Eric|title=Grammys 2014: Watch Detroit Red Bull House of Art 'City of Soldiers' commercial aired during show|url=http://www.mlive.com/entertainment/detroit/index.ssf/2014/01/grammys_2014_watch_detroit_red.html|publisher=MLive|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Sports sponsorships and acquisitions===\n{{seealsocat|Red Bull sports teams}}\n* [[Red Bull Racing]]\u2014a [[Formula One]] team based in [[Milton Keynes]], England, World Constructor's Championship winner of 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013, and produced the car for the 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013 F1 World Champion [[Sebastian Vettel]].\n* [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]] (Named after Red Bull's fashion brand [[AlphaTauri (fashion brand)|AlphaTauri]]): Another Formula One team based in [[Faenza]], Italy, considered Red Bull's \u201cjunior\u201d team\n* [[RB Leipzig]]: a [[Association football|football]] club currently playing in the German [[Bundesliga|1. Bundesliga]]\n* [[New York Red Bulls]]: a [[Association football|football]] franchise competing in [[Major League Soccer]] of the United States.\n* [[Red Bull Sailing Team]]: an [[Extreme Sailing Series]] racing team.\n* [[Team Red Bull]]: a Toyota racing team competing in the U.S.-based stock car racing competition [[NASCAR]] Red Bull Racing Team competed in NASCAR beginning in 2007. The team ceased operations after the Sprint Cup Series' 2011 season.\n* [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]]: an Austrian football club based in Salzburg and competing in the [[Austrian Bundesliga]]\n* [[EC Red Bull Salzburg]]: a member of the [[Austrian Hockey League]] based in Salzburg, Austria\n* [[EHC Red Bull M\u00fcnchen]]: a member of the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] based in [[Munich]], Germany\n* [[Red Bull Brasil]]: a football club which played in the Brazilian [[Campeonato Paulista]] based in [[Campinas]], Brazil before merging with [[Bragantino]] in 2019.\n[[File:Shane van Gisbergen at Sydney Motorsport Park.jpg|thumb|200px|2017 [[Holden Commodore]] #97 of [[Shane van Gisbergen]] of the [[Triple Eight Race Engineering|Red Bull Holden Racing Team]]]]\n* [[Triple Eight Race Engineering|Red Bull Holden Racing Team]] \u2013 a [[Supercars Championship|Supercars]] team run by Triple Eight Race Engineering, manufacturer of cars 88 driven by seven-time champion [[Jamie Whincup]] and 97 driven by [[2016 International V8 Supercars Championship|2016]] champion [[Shane van Gisbergen]] \u2013 Red Bull had sponsored the team as Red Bull Racing Australia, from [[2013 International V8 Supercars Championship|2013]] until [[2017 International V8 Supercars Championship|2017]], when the team was given sole factory backing from [[Holden]], rebranding as the Red Bull Holden Racing Team.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.supercars.com/news/championship/holden-commits-to-supercars/|title=Holden commits to Supercars {{!}} Supercars|work=Supercars|access-date=2017-10-15}}</ref>\n* Red Bull Racing Brasil, a [[Stock Car Brasil]] team, from 2007 to 2017.\n* [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]], a team competing in [[Grand Prix motorcycle racing|MotoGP]]. \n* [[Red Bull Ghana]]: was a Ghanaian professional football club located in Sogakope that played in the [[Ghana Football Leagues|Poly Tank Division One League]].\n* [[\u0160koda Motorsport]] [[rallying|rally]] team\n* [[Red Bulls]], a [[League of Legends]] team currently playing in the [[League of Legends Challenger Series#Europe|European League of Legends Challenger Series]]\n* Esports team [[OG Dota 2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.redbull.com/za-en/og-announcement |title=OG and the rise of player centred teams |publisher=redbull.com |access-date=2017-08-02}}</ref>\n\n===Sponsorships===\n[[File:Audi Abt Sportsline.jpg|thumb|Audi A4 DTM, which won the Manufacturers' championship in 2004]]\n[[File:Kimi R\u00e4ikk\u00f6nen - 2010 Rally Bulgaria.jpg|thumb|The Citro\u00ebn rally car, which won the manufacturers' title in 2008, 2009 and 2010.]]\n[[File:Mika Kallio.jpg|thumb|A Red Bull sponsored track racing bike]]\n[[File:Hangar7-01.jpg|thumb|A Sauber C15 from 1995 in display at Red Bull Hangar-7]]\n[[File:Dakar car 2007.jpg|thumb|A VW Touareg during the Dakar Rally, which won the event in 2009, 2010 and 2011]]\n[[File:Antonio_Cairoli_ITA_FMI_Yamaha_FIM_MX_Mallory_Park_2008_R6a.jpg|thumb|Antonio Cairoli, which won the motocross world championship in 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2017]]\n* [[100 Thieves]]\n* [[Abt Sportsline]] \n* [[Arrows Grand Prix International|Arrows]] F1 team from 2001 to 2002\n* [[Audi Sport]] for the A4 DTM\n* Batalla de los Gallos\n* [[Cac\u00e1 Bueno]]'s speed record Vectra\n* [[Carlin Motorsport]] Dallara-Renault\n* [[Citro\u00ebn World Rally Team]] (2008\u20132012)\n* [[Cloud9]] ''League of Legends'' eSports team\n* [[EKS RX]]\n* [[Ford Fiesta WRC]]\n* [[G2 eSports]]''League of Legends'' eSports team\n* [[Hansen Motorsport]] rallycross team\n* [[Hyundai Genesis Coupe]] Pikes Peak edition\n* [[Hyundai Veloster]] rallycross car\n* [[Kamaz]] Dakar rally trucks\n* [[JMB Racing]] Maserati MC12 GT\n* [[KTM]] road, MXGP and Dakar rally bikes\n* Red Bull [[Ajo Motorsport]]\n* Red Bull Youth America's Cup\n* [[Repsol Honda|Repsol Honda Team]]\n* [[OG (eSports)|OG]] ''Dota 2'' eSports team\n* Oracle Team USA\n* [[Olsbergs MSE]] Ford rallycross team\n* [[Peugeot 208]] T16\n* [[Peugeot 2008 DKR]] (2015)\n* [[Sauber]] F1 team (1995\u20132004)\n* [[SEAT Sport]] WTCC team\n* [[\u0160koda Fabia S2000]]\n* [[Ten Kate Racing|Red Bull Honda World Superbike Team]]\n* [[Volkswagen Passat]] [[DARPA Grand Challenge]] edition\n* Andrew Dickson, pro BMX rider \n* [[Volkswagen Polo R WRC]]\n* [[Volkswagen Race Touareg]] Dakar edition\n* [[Volkswagen Touareg|Volkswagen V10 TDI Touaregs Pikes Peak edition]]\n\n===Endorsements===\nIn 2009, Red Bull added mainstream sport athletes to its roster of endorsements, which also includes persons involved in non-sporting activities.\n\n* [[Reggie Bush]], US NFL athlete announced at the [[Super Bowl XLIV|2009 Super Bowl]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espnmag/story?id=3873150 |title=Reggie Bush Goes to Red Bull&nbsp;\u2013 ESPN The Magazine |publisher=Sports.espn.go.com |access-date=2009-06-22|date=2009-01-30 }}</ref>\n*[[Ryan Dungey]] American Supercross, Motocross rider for [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]].\n**\n*[[Marvin Musquin]] French Supercross, Motocross rider for [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]].\n**\n* [[Dani Pedrosa]], [[Marc M\u00e1rquez]], [[John Reynolds (motorcycle racer)|John Reynolds]], [[Andrea Dovizioso]], [[Casey Stoner]], and [[Nicky Hayden]]\n* [[Red Bull Junior Team]], a program which sponsors young drivers competing in [[Single seater racing car|single seater racing]]. Since 2001 many young drivers developed careers in professional motorsport, with 13 participants having competed in Formula One, including quadruple F1 world champion [[Sebastian Vettel]], [[Daniel Ricciardo]], and [[Max Verstappen]]\n* Skijumpers [[Gregor Schlierenzauer]], [[Thomas Morgenstern]], [[Adam Ma\u0142ysz]], and [[Andreas Goldberger]], snowboarders [[Mark McMorris]], [[Torah Bright]] and [[Nathan Johnstone]], and skiers [[Kaya Turski]], [[Lindsey Vonn]], [[Axel Lund Svindal]] and [[Alexis Pinturault]].\n* [[Dion Phaneuf]] NHL defenseman\n* Young professional golfer [[Rickie Fowler]].\n* Racing driver [[Andrew Jordan (racing driver)|Andrew Jordan]].\n* Drift racing driver [[\"Mad\" Mike Whiddett]].\n* Professional chess player [[Hikaru Nakamura]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/uk/en/athletes/1331689033551/hikaru-nakamura|title=Hikaru Nakamura Always try to win at all costs|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uschess.org/content/view/12630/760/|title=The United States Chess Federation - US #1 Nakamura Signs with Red Bull|website=www.uschess.org|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n* ''[[Super Smash Bros. Melee]]'' player [[William \"Leffen\" Hjelte]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/us/en/esports/stories/1331777065928/how-leffen-will-take-over-smash-bros|title=How Leffen Will Take Over the World|first=Barrett|last=Womack|website=Red Bull eSports|date=16 February 2016}}</ref>\n* ''[[Street Fighter]]'' players [[Daigo Umehara]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/daigo-signs-with-red-bull-as-mad-catz-officially-exits-player-sponsorship-605a0560e0e6#.x495rv4do|title=Daigo signs with Red Bull as Mad Catz officially exits player sponsorship|website=[[The Daily Dot|Dot]] Esports|date=16 May 2016|access-date=2016-11-26}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Masato \"Bonchan\" Takahashi,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/japanese-fighting-game-legend-bonchan-joins-red-bull-64a977e96f9a#.3eoixpnns|title=Japanese fighting game legend Bonchan joins Red Bull|website=Dot Esports|date=1 September 2015|access-date=2016-11-26}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> [[Darryl \"Snake Eyez\" Lewis]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shoryuken.com/2015/07/22/red-bull-gives-darryl-snake-eyez-lewis-wings/|title=Red Bull Gives Darryl \"Snake Eyez\" Lewis Wings|website=Shoryuken.com|last=Walker|first=Ian|date=22 July 2015|access-date=2016-11-26}}</ref> [[Olivier \"Luffy\" Hay]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/luffy-signs-with-red-bull-4ee090ed6cda#.uly15ez1i|title=Luffy signs with Red Bull|website=Dot Esports|date=14 February 2016|access-date=2016-11-26}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Adel \"Big Bird\" Anouche,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shoryuken.com/2018/01/09/adel-big-bird-anouche-is-the-latest-street-fighter-v-player-to-join-red-bulls-athlete-program/|title=Adel \"Big Bird\" Anouche is the latest Street Fighter V player to join Red Bull's Athlete program|website=Shoryuken|date=29 January 2018|access-date=2018-12-16}}</ref> and Tsunehiro \"Gachikun\" Kanamori.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shoryuken.com/2018/11/07/tsunehiro-gachikun-kanamori-becomes-a-red-bull-athlete/|title=Tsunehiro \"Gachikun\" Kanamori becomes a Red Bull Athlete|website=Shoryuken|date=7 November 2018|access-date=2018-12-16}}</ref> \n* League of Legends player [[XPeke|Enrique Cede\u00f1o Martinez (xPeke)]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://origen.gg/2015/05/xpeke-becomes-a-red-bull-athlete/|title=xPeke becomes a Red Bull Athlete|last=Origen staff|date=14 May 2015|access-date=2017-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621194356/http://origen.gg/2015/05/xpeke-becomes-a-red-bull-athlete/|archive-date=21 June 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.summoners-inn.de/de/news/28269-xpeke-ist-der-erste-redbull-athlet|title=xPeke ist der erste RedBull-Athlet!|last=Galaflow|date=15 May 2015|website=Summoners-Inn.de|language=de|access-date=2017-06-30}}</ref>\n* [[Trail running|Trail runners]] [[Ryan Sandes]] and Ryno Griesel at the [[Great Himalaya Trails#High Route|Great Himalaya Trail]]\n*Four times [[IHF World Player of the Year]] winner  [[Cristina Neagu]]\n\n===Events===\n[[File:Red Bull Flugtag 1 2010.jpg|thumb|Red Bull Flugtag Stockholm 2010]]\n[[File:Red Bull Flugtag 1.5 2010.jpg|thumb|Red Bull Flugtag Stockholm 2010]]\n* [[:Category:Red Bull sports events|Red Bull sports events]]\n* Red Bull 400\n* Red Bull Battle Grounds: An [[eSports]] competition in popular video games ''[[Dota 2]]'' and ''[[StarCraft 2]]''\n* [[Red Bull Stratos]]\n* [[Red Bull Straight Rhythm]]\n* [[Red Bull Double Pipe]]\n* [[Global Rallycross|Red Bull Global Rallycross Championship]]\n* [[Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series]]\n* [[Red Bull Drifting World Championship]]\n* [[Red Bull Rampage]]\n* [[Red Bull Road Rage]]\n* [[Red Bull King of the Rock Tournament]]\n* [[Red Bull Romaniacs Hard Enduro Rallye]]\n* [[Red Bull Crashed Ice]]\n* [[Red Bull X-Fighters]]\n* [[Red Bull X-Alps]]\n* [[Red Bull Air Race World Championship]]\n* [[Red Bull Flugtag]]\n* Red Bull [[Frozen Rush]]\n* Red Bull Foxhunt\n* [[Red Bull Cape Fear]]\n* [[Red Bull Paperwings]]\n* Red Bull Training Grounds<ref>{{cite web|title=Breaking Down The Elite Eight :: Red Bull Esports|url=http://www.redbull.com/us/en/esports/stories/1331597749419/breaking-down-the-elite-eight|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2013-06-21}}</ref>\n* [[Red Bull Art of Motion]]\n* [[Red Bull BC One]]\n* Red Bull Cold Rush<ref>{{cite web|title=Red Bull Cold Rush 2012 :: Red Bull|url=http://www.redbullusa.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Red-Bull-Cold-Rush-2012/001243163633447|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2012-04-17}}</ref>\n* [[Dolomitenmann|Red Bull Dolomitenmann]] \u2013 A 4-man relay competition including trail running, paragliding, kayaking, mountainbiking<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dolomitenmann.com/ |title=Red Bull Dolomitenmann &#124; |publisher=Dolomitenmann.com |date=3 April 2013 |access-date=2013-07-28}}</ref>\n* Red Bull Elements \u2013 A 4-man relay competition including rowing, trail running, paragliding, mountainbiking<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.redbullelements.com/ |title=Red Bull Elements |publisher=Red Bull Aventure |access-date=2013-11-13 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* [[Red Bull MotoGP Rookies Cup]]\n* [[Indianapolis motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n* [[Motorcycle Grand Prix of the Americas]]\n* [[Argentine motorcycle Grand Prix]] (2014\u20132015)\n* [[Spanish motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n* Red Bull Storm Chase \u2013 A worldwide windsurfing competition in storm conditions with wind speeds of at least force ten<ref>{{cite web|title=Red Bull Storm Chase|url=http://www.redbullstormchase.com|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2014-02-09}}</ref>\n* Red Bull Supernatural \u2013 A \"backcountry boarding competition designed to challenge, then crown the best all-around snowboarder on the planet.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/Event/Red-Bull-Supernatural-021243151773398|title=Red Bull Supernatural Event Web Page|access-date=2012-08-22}}</ref>\n* [[Red Bull Soapbox Race]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://soapbox.redbull.co.uk |title=Red Bull Soapbox Race |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126071926/http://soapbox.redbull.co.uk/ |archive-date=26 January 2013 |access-date=2013-02-07 }}</ref>\n* [[Red Bull Unleashed]] \u2013 A surfing event at [[Surf Snowdonia]], north Wales<ref>{{cite news |title=Red Bull Unleashed 2015|url=https://www.redbull.com/gb-en/events/red-bull-unleashed-2015|work=Red Bull|access-date=17 November 2018}}</ref>\n* Red Bull World Bridge Series<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldbridge.org/2014-world-bridge-series.aspx |title=2014 World Bridge Series \u2013 World Bridge Federation |publisher=Worldbridge.org |date=24 July 2013 |access-date=2014-06-10}}</ref>\n* Red Bull Drift Shifters \u2013 Drifting event held on a pinball inspired street course in Auckland, New Zealand\n* [[Red Bull Music Academy]]\n* Red Bull Can You Make It\n* Red Bull Timelaps\n\n[[File:Vonn-lindsey 08-03-08 - 008.jpg|thumb|Red Bull-sponsored Lindsey Vonn won four World Cup alpine ski racing championships]]\n\n===Locations===\n* [[Red Bull Ring]], a motorsport circuit in Spielberg, Styria, Austria.\n* [[Red Bull Arena (Leipzig)]], home stadium of German football club RB Leipzig.\n* [[Red Bull Arena (New Jersey)]], home stadium of the American soccer club New York Red Bulls.\n* [[Red Bull Arena (Salzburg)]], home stadium of Austrian football club FC Red Bull Salzburg.\n* [[Hangar-7|Hangar-7 (Salzburg)]], a multifunctional building with a collection of historical airplanes.\n* Red Bull bridge, a recurring distinctly branded footbridge at race events such as the [[World Enduro Championship]] and [[Rally Deutschland]].\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portalbar|Drink}}\n* [[Krating Daeng]]\n* [[Felix Baumgartner#Red Bull Stratos|Felix Baumgartner]] \u2014 stratospheric parachute jump 2012\n*[[Red Bull GmbH]]\n*[[Dietrich Mateschitz]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.redbull.com}}\n\n{{Red Bull}}\n{{Energy drinks}}\n{{Streamy Awards Winners CSS}}\n\n[[Category:Red Bull| ]]\n[[Category:Austrian brands]]\n[[Category:Food and drink companies of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1987]]\n[[Category:Thai brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Energy drink sold by Austrian company Red Bull GmbH}}\n{{about|the energy drink|the company|Red Bull GmbH|other uses|Red Bull (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{infobox beverage\n|logo         = RedBullEnergyDrink.svg\n|type         = [[Energy drink]]\n|proof        =\n|distributor  = [[Red Bull GmbH]]\n|origin       = [[Austria]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Who makes Red Bull? Red Bull Company - Origin & founder :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull USA |url=https://energydrink-us.redbull.com/en/company |website=energydrink-us.redbull.com |access-date=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n|introduced   = 1987\n|color       = Amber\n|ingredients = [[Caffeine]], [[taurine]],<ref>https://escholarship.org/content/qt65k8r3bd/qt65k8r3bd.pdf</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://escholarship.org/uc/item/65k8r3bd|title=Debunking the Effects of Taurine in Red Bull Energy Drink|first=Woojae|last=Kim|date=18 March 2003|journal=Nutrition Bytes|volume=9|issue=1|accessdate=18 March 2020|via=escholarship.org}}</ref> [[glucuronolactone]],<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A taurine and caffeine-containing drink stimulates cognitive performance and well-being|first1=R.|last1=Seidl|first2=A.|last2=Peyrl|first3=R.|last3=Nicham|first4=E.|last4=Hauser|date=18 March 2000|journal=Amino Acids|volume=19|issue=3\u20134|pages=635\u2013642|doi=10.1007/s007260070013|pmid=11140366}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Energy drink ingredients. Contribution of caffeine and taurine to performance outcomes|first1=Amy|last1=Peacock|first2=Frances Heritage|last2=Martin|first3=Andrea|last3=Carr|date=1 May 2013|journal=Appetite|volume=64|pages=1\u20134|doi=10.1016/j.appet.2012.12.021|pmid=23313701}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Taurine, caffeine, and energy drinks: Reviewing the risks to the adolescent brain|first1=Christine Perdan|last1=Curran|first2=Cecile A.|last2=Marczinski|date=1 December 2017|journal=Birth Defects Research|volume=109|issue=20|pages=1640\u20131648|doi=10.1002/bdr2.1177|pmid=29251842|pmc=5737830}}</ref> [[sucrose]] and [[glucose]], [[B vitamins|B-group vitamins]], and [[Spring (hydrology)|alpine spring water]]\n|variants     = [[#Flavours|Over 20]]\n|related      = [[Krating Daeng]], [[Red Bull Simply Cola|Red Bull Cola]], Red Bull Energy Shot, Red Bull Sugar-Free, Red Bull Total Zero\n|website      = {{URL|redbull.com}}\n}}\n'''Red Bull''' is an [[energy drink]] sold by [[Red Bull GmbH]], an Austrian company created in 1987. Red Bull has the highest market share of any energy drink in the world, with 6.790&nbsp;billion cans sold in a year ({{As of|2018|lc=y}}).<ref name=\"CompanyWebsite\">{{cite web|title=Who makes Red Bull|url=http://energydrink-us.redbull.com/company|first=Adam|last=Boome|date=31 May 2011|website=|access-date=30 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304204033/http://energydrink-us.redbull.com/company|archive-date=4 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Energy Drinks Build Their Buzz|url=http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/jan2005/sb2005015_8196_sb017.htm|work=BloombergBusinessweek|publisher=BLOOMBERG L.P|access-date=2012-08-19|author=Burt Helm|date=4 January 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Company Figures|url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/company-figures/001242939605518?pcs_c=PCS_Product&pcs_cid=1242937556133|work=Red Bull|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2012-08-19|author=Red Bull|year=2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://energydrink.redbull.com/company |title=Red Bull the company \u2013 Who makes Red Bull? Red Bull Origin :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull |publisher=Energydrink.redbull.com |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref>\n\nAustrian entrepreneur [[Dietrich Mateschitz]] was inspired by an existing energy drink named [[Krating Daeng]], which was first introduced and sold in [[Thailand]] by [[Chaleo Yoovidhya]]. He took this idea, modified the ingredients to suit the tastes of Westerners,<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VrO3O0h6I0wC |title=Asian Brand Strategy: How Asia Builds Strong Brands |last1=Roll |first1=Martin |isbn=9780230513068 |page=199 |publisher=Springer |date=17 October 2005 |access-date=2012-09-24}}</ref> and, in partnership with Chaleo, founded Red Bull&nbsp;GmbH in 1987 in Chakkapong, Thailand. In [[Thai language|Thai]], ''daeng'' means red, and a ''[[gaur|krating]]'' (known in English as a gaur or Indian bison) is a large species of wild [[bovine]] native to South Asia. Yoovidhya's heirs own majority stakes in both brands, and they both use the same red bull on yellow sun logo while continuing to market the separate drinks to the respective Thai and Western markets.\n\nRed Bull is sold in a tall and slim blue-silver can.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former F1 Driver David Coulthard Thrilled Shoppers Along Bukit Bintang in Red Bull Racings Show Car Run|url=http://www.cheryl-tay.com/news/former-f1-driver-david-coulthard-thrilled-shoppers-along-bukit-bintang-in-red-bull-racings-show-car-run.html|work=Va Va Vroom|publisher=Cheryl Tay Pte Ltd.|access-date=2012-07-27|author=Cheryl Tay|date=8 April 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108082847/http://cheryl-tay.com/news/former-f1-driver-david-coulthard-thrilled-shoppers-along-bukit-bintang-in-red-bull-racings-show-car-run.html|archive-date=8 January 2012}}</ref> Originally only available in a single nondescript flavor and regular or [[Diet soda|sugar-free formulas]], a line of \"color editions\" with artificial fruit flavors were added to the line beginning in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/chicago/news/2013/02/28/red-bull-ready-to-introduce-new-flavors.html|title=Red Bull introduces new flavors|first=Lewis|last=Lazare|work=American CIty Business Journals|date=28 February 2013|access-date=6 May 2018}}</ref> The Red Bull company slogan is \"Red Bull gives you wings\",<ref name=\"company\">{{cite web|url=http://authoring.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Products/Company-021242755317296|title=Company|work=Red Bull|access-date=2011-04-02|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130201063750/http://authoring.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_US/Products/Company-021242755317296|archive-date=1 February 2013}}</ref> occasionally \"No Red Bull, no wings\". Rather than following a traditional approach to mass marketing, Red Bull has generated awareness and created a 'brand myth'<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kuehlwein|first1= JP|last2 =Chaefer|first2= Wolf|title=How modern prestige brands create meaning through mission and myth|journal=Journal of Brand Strategy|volume=5|issue=4|date= Spring 2017}}{{ISSN|2045-855X}}</ref><ref>Kuehlwein, JP. [https://masstoclass.wordpress.com/2015/12/15/ueber-brands-and-the-art-of-myth-making/ Ueber-Brands and The Art of Myth-Making]. www.ueberbrands.com 12/2015</ref> through proprietary extreme sport event series such as [[Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series]], [[Red Bull Air Race]], [[Crashed Ice|Red Bull Crashed Ice]] and stand-out stunts such as the [[Red Bull Stratos|Stratos space diving project]].<ref>Schaefer, Wolf and Kuehlwein, JP. 2015. Rethinking Prestige Branding \u2013 Secrets of the Ueber-Brands. Kogan Page. pp.77ff. {{ISBN|9780749470036}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull's marketing also includes multiple sports team ownerships ([[Formula One]] teams [[Red Bull Racing]] and [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]], [[Association football|football]] clubs [[RB Leipzig]], [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]], [[FC Liefering]], [[Red Bull Brasil]] and [[New York Red Bulls]]), celebrity endorsements, and music, through its record label [[Red Bull Records]].<ref name=\"Pump the Music\">{{Cite news|title=Pump the Music: Red Bull Eyes Starting Branded Music Label&nbsp;\u2014 NYPost.com|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/item_SY9XQMYwCgtsf6cCoINAOO;jsessionid=A41FF58821B638E4FD7E126596BCABFB|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130130130346/http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/item_SY9XQMYwCgtsf6cCoINAOO;jsessionid=A41FF58821B638E4FD7E126596BCABFB|url-status=dead|archive-date=30 January 2013|work=New York Post|first=Peter|last=Lauria|date=1 April 2008}}101013 NYPost.com</ref>\n\nEnergy drinks have been associated with health risks, such as masking the effects of [[Alcohol intoxication|intoxication]] when consumed with alcohol,<ref name=\"AFP2011\">{{Cite web|title = Combining energy drinks and alcohol|vauthors=Pennay A, Lubman DI, Miller P |date = 2011|access-date = 2015-08-12|url = http://www.racgp.org.au/download/documents/AFP/2011/March/201103pennay.pdf}}</ref> and excessive or repeated consumption can lead to cardiac and psychiatric conditions.<ref name=\"pmid25818530\"/><ref name=\"pmid25622514\"/> However, the [[European Food Safety Authority|European Food Safety Authority (EFSA)]] concluded that an adequate consumption of Red Bull and other popular energy drinks is safe and that the amount of caffeine in a standard Red Bull can is unlikely to interact adversely with other typical constituents of energy drinks or with alcohol.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Scientific Opinion on the safety of caffeine {{!}} Europ\u00e4ische Beh\u00f6rde f\u00fcr Lebensmittelsicherheit|url = http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/efsajournal/pub/4102|website = www.efsa.europa.eu|access-date = 2016-01-02|date = 2015-05-27}}</ref> Energy drinks have the effects that caffeine and sugar give, but there is no distinct evidence that the wide variety of other ingredients has any effect.<ref name=\"pmid23206286\"/>\n\n==History==\n\n[[File:Red Bull near Potala Palace.jpg|thumb|In front of the [[Potala Palace]], Tibet: a model of Red Bull in Chinese version is displayed.]]\n[[File:Red Bull Car in Israel (1).jpg|thumb|Red Bull car]]\n\nIn 1976, [[Chaleo Yoovidhya]] introduced a drink called [[Krating Daeng]] in Thailand, which means \"red [[gaur]]\" in English. It was popular among Thai truck drivers and labourers. While working for German manufacturer Blendax (later acquired by [[Procter & Gamble]]) in 1982, [[Dietrich Mateschitz]] travelled to Thailand and met Chaleo, owner of T.C. Pharmaceutical. During his visit, Mateschitz discovered that Krating Daeng helped cure his [[jet lag]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/people/displayStory.cfm?story_id=1120373 |title=Face value &#124; Selling energy |publisher=Economist.com |date=9 May 2002 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref> In 1984, Mateschitz co-founded [[Red Bull GmbH]] with Yoovidhya and turned it into an international brand. Each partner invested US$500,000 of savings to found the company. Yoovidhya and Mateschitz each held a 49 percent share of the new company. They gave the remaining two percent to Yoovidhya's son, Chalerm, but it was agreed that Mateschitz would run the company.<ref name=\"forbes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2005/0328/028_print.html|title=The Soda With Buzz|date=28 March 2005|author=Kerry A. Dolan|work=Forbes|access-date=20 June 2015}}</ref> The product was launched in Austria in 1987.\n\nIn Thailand, energy drinks are most popular with blue-collar workers. Red Bull re-positioned the drink as a trendy, upscale drink, first introducing it at Austrian ski resorts. Pricing was a key differentiator, with Red Bull positioned as a premium drink and Krating Daeng as a lower cost item. In many countries, both drinks are available, dominating both ends of the price spectrum.<ref name=BP-20151228 />\n\nIn 1992, the product expanded to [[Hungary]] and [[Slovenia]].<ref name=\"funding universe history\">{{cite web| title = Red Bull GmbH Company History | url = http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/Red-Bull-GmbH-Company-History.html | publisher = Funding Universe | access-date = 2007-10-12}}</ref> It entered Germany and the UK in 1994,<ref name=\"funding universe history\"/> the United States (via California) in 1997<ref name=\"funding universe history\"/> and the Middle East in 2000.<ref>{{Cite news| author = Ligaya, Armina | title = Region abuzz over energy drinks | work = [[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]] | date = 12 May 2010 | page = Business section, pp. 1, 6 | url = http://www.thenational.ae/business/retail/region-abuzz-over-energy-drinks | access-date = 2010-05-13}}</ref> In 2008, ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine listed both Chaleo and Mateschitz as the 250th&nbsp;richest people in the world with an estimated net worth of US$4&nbsp;billion.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_The-Worlds-Billionaires_CountryOfPrmRes_23.html |title=The World's Billionaires |magazine=Forbes.com |date=11 February 2008 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_The-Worlds-Billionaires_CountryOfPrmRes.html |title=The World's Billionaires |magazine=Forbes.com |date=11 February 2008 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull GmbH is headquartered in [[Fuschl am See]], an Austrian village of about 1,500 inhabitants near [[Salzburg]]. The company is 51 percent controlled by the Yoovidhya family who, for technical reasons, own the trademark in Europe and the US.<ref name=BP-20151228>{{cite news|last1=Nivatpumin|first1=Chiratas|last2=Treeraponpichit|first2=Busrin|title=Red Bull still charging ahead |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/business/news/808868/red-bull-still-charging-ahead|access-date=30 December 2015|work=Bangkok Post|date=28 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 1995, [[Krating Daeng]] authorized its drink, labelled as Red Bull, to be sold in [[People's Republic of China|China]]. Since 2014, the Austrian Red Bull (carbonated) has also been exported to China. This has created confusion since both drinks use the same brand name, in both English and Chinese.\n\nSimilarly, in Southeast Asia, Red Bull and Krating Daeng are often confused as both use the Red Bull name in their packaging, although they are two separate products aimed at different markets. The main difference is that Red Bull comes in a tall blue and silver can while the [[Thailand]] Red Bull, or Krating Daeng, is in a smaller gold can. The two drinks also differ in terms of taste\u2014Red Bull has less sugar and is carbonated. The flavouring used for Red Bull is still produced in Bangkok and exported worldwide.<ref name=BP-20151228 />\n\n==Ingredients==\n{{replace|{{Infobox nutritional value\n| name            = \n| image           = <!-- Filename is enough -->\n| image_size      = <!-- Defaults to 235px -->\n| image_alt       = \n| caption         = \n| serving_size    = 100 mL<ref name=\"can photo\">{{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/bM8Yl2Ar.jpg|title=Enerji \u0130\u00e7ece\u011fi|format=photography of part of the can with nutrition information, BiH import|lang=tr|date=16 September 2019|accessdate=16 September 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916100514/https://i.imgur.com/bM8Yl2Ar.jpg|archivedate=16 September 2019}}</ref>\n| kJ              = 205\n| carbs           = 11.3\n| starch          = \n| sugars          = 11.3\n| lactose         = \n| fiber           = <!-- or |fibre= -->\n| fat             = 0\n| satfat          = 0\n| transfat        = \n| monofat         = \n| polyfat         = \n| omega3fat       = \n| omega6fat       = \n| protein         = 0\n| tryptophan      = \n| threonine       = \n| isoleucine      = \n| leucine         = \n| lysine          = \n| methionine      = \n| cystine         = \n| phenylalanine   = \n| tyrosine        = \n| valine          = \n| arginine        = \n| histidine       = \n| alanine         = \n| aspartic acid   = \n| glutamic acid   = \n| glycine         = \n| proline         = \n| serine          = \n| hydroxyproline  = \n| water           = \n| cholesterol     = \n| alcohol         = \n| caffeine        = \n| vitA_ug         = \n| vitA_iu         = \n| betacarotene_ug = \n| lutein_ug       = \n| thiamin_mg      = \n| riboflavin_mg   = \n| niacin_mg       = 8.0\n| pantothenic_mg  = 2.0\n| vitB6_mg        = 2.0\n| folate_ug       = \n| vitB12_ug       = 2.0\n| choline_mg      = \n| vitC_mg         = \n| vitD_ug         = \n| vitD_iu         = \n| vitE_mg         = \n| vitK_ug         = \n| calcium_mg      = \n| copper_mg       = \n| iron_mg         = \n| magnesium_mg    = \n| manganese_mg    = \n| phosphorus_mg   = \n| potassium_mg    = \n| selenium_ug     =\n| sodium_mg       = \n| zinc_mg         = \n| opt1n           = [[Salt]]s\n| opt1v           = 0.205 g\n| opt2n           = [[Taurine]]\n| opt2v           = 80 mg\n| opt3n           = [[Caffeine]]\n| opt3v           = 15 mg\n| opt4n           = \n| opt4v           = \n| note            = \n| source          = \n| source_usda     = \n| noRDA           = \n| float           = right\n}}|Nutritional value|{{abbr|Nutritional value|Red&thinsp;Bull Energy Drink, Enerji \u0130\u00e7ece\u011fi [Turkish production]}}}}\n\nDepending on the country, Red Bull contains different amounts of [[caffeine]], [[taurine]], [[B vitamins]] (B3, B5, B6, B12) and simple sugars ([[sucrose]] and [[glucose]]) in a [[buffer solution]] of [[carbonated water]], [[sodium bicarbonate|baking soda]] and [[magnesium carbonate]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Red Bull Ingredients :: Energy Drink :: Red Bull |url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/Red-Bull-Energy-Drink/001242937921959?pcs_c=PCS_Product&pcs_cid=1242937842064&pcs_pvt=ingredient|publisher=Red Bull|access-date=2012-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.caffeineinformer.com/caffeine-content/red-bull|title=Caffeine in Red Bull|website=www.caffeineinformer.com|access-date=2017-12-29}}</ref> To produce Red Bull Sugarfree, sugars sucrose and glucose have been replaced by the sweeteners [[acesulfame K]] and [[aspartame]]/[[sucralose]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redbull.com/cs/Satellite/en_INT/Red-Bull-Sugarfree/001242937921959?pcs_cid=1242937877523&pcs_pvt=ingredient&pcs_iid=1243128878373 |title=Sweeteners in Red Bull zero sugar? :: Energy drink sugar free |publisher=Red Bull |access-date=2012-09-24}}</ref> \n\nPrevious formulations of Red Bull contained 0.24% [[glucuronolactone]] (600 mg of glucuronolactone in a 250 ml can),<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Alford|first=C.|last2=Cox|first2=H.|last3=Wescott|first3=R.|date=2001|title=The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood|journal=Amino Acids|volume=21|issue=2|pages=139\u2013150|issn=0939-4451|pmid=11665810|doi=10.1007/s007260170021}}</ref> but this ingredient was removed.\n\n==Flavours==\nRed Bull identifies its flavours as \"editions\".\n\n===Current===\n*Original (amber)\n*Sugar-free (5 calories)\n*Total Zero (no calories)\n*Red (cranberry)\n*Ruby/Red (grapefruit)\n*Blue (blueberry)\n*Yellow/Tropical (tropical fruit/mango papaya)\n*Orange/Mandarin (mandarin/orange/orange-[[kumquat]])\n*Green/Kiwi (kiwi-apple)\n*White/Coconut (coconut berry)\n*Peach (peach-nectarine)\n*Pear Sugar-Free (pear)\n*Lime Sugar-Free (lime)\n*Purple/Acai Sugar-Free (a\u00e7ai)\n*Purple/Acai (acai berry)\n*Lime (lime-lemon)\n*Orange Sugar-free (orange) \n*Yellow/Tropical Sugar-free (tropical)\n*Winter (plum twist)\n*Summer Edition Beach Breeze (2019) (azure can, coconut/tutti-frutti)\n\n===Discontinued===\n*Silver (dry lime)\n*Spring Edition (sakura cherry)\n*Orange Total Zero (orange)\n*Cherry Total Zero (wild cherry)\n*Blue Edition (grape)\n\nSeveral of these flavors have been rebranded for special events (the special grapefruit flavor, for example, has been branded as the \"Bull\" Edition, the \"Red Italian\" Edition, and the \"[[Formula 1|F1]] Edition\").\n\n==Health effects==\n{{further|Energy drinks#Effects}}\nClaims about the drink's effects and performance have been challenged on various occasions, with the UK's [[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] imposing advertising restrictions in 2001 in response to complaints recorded as early as 1997.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/1133348.stm |title=HEALTH &#124; Energy drink claims rejected |work=BBC News |date=24 January 2001 |access-date=2009-06-22}}</ref>\n\nEnergy drinks have the effects that caffeine and sugar provide, but experts still argue about the possible effects of the other [[ingredients]].<ref name=\"pmid23206286\">{{cite journal | vauthors = McLellan TM, Lieberman HR | title = Do energy drinks contain active components other than caffeine? | journal = Nutrition Reviews | volume = 70 | issue = 12 | pages = 730\u201344 | date = December 2012 | pmid = 23206286 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1111/j.1753-4887.2012.00525.x }}</ref> Most of the effects of energy drinks on cognitive performance, such as increased attention and reaction speed, are primarily due to the presence of caffeine.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite journal | vauthors = van den Eynde F, van Baelen PC, Portzky M, Audenaert K | title = [The effects of energy drinks on cognitive performance] | journal = Tijdschrift voor Psychiatrie | volume = 50 | issue = 5 | pages = 273\u201381 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18470842 }}</ref> There is evidence that energy drinks can increase mental<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Alford C, Cox H, Wescott R | title = The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 21 | issue = 2 | pages = 139\u201350 | date = 1 January 2001 | pmid = 11665810 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170021 | url = http://eprints.uwe.ac.uk/96/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Tijdschrift voor Psychiatrie - Author index: Baelen, P.C. van |url=http://www.tijdschriftvoorpsychiatrie.nl/en/zoeken/artikel.php?autid=2007&pgr=0 |date=21 December 2008 |access-date=2016-02-02 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081221221448/http://www.tijdschriftvoorpsychiatrie.nl/en/zoeken/artikel.php?autid=2007&pgr=0 |archive-date=21 December 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mets MA, Ketzer S, Blom C, van Gerven MH, van Willigenburg GM, Olivier B, Verster JC | title = Positive effects of Red Bull\u00ae Energy Drink on driving performance during prolonged driving | journal = Psychopharmacology | volume = 214 | issue = 3 | pages = 737\u201345 | date = April 2011 | pmid = 21063868 | pmc = 3053448 | doi = 10.1007/s00213-010-2078-2 }}</ref> and athletic<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Baum M, Weiss M | title = The influence of a taurine containing drink on cardiac parameters before and after exercise measured by echocardiography | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 20 | issue = 1 | pages = 75\u201382 | date = 1 January 2001 | pmid = 11310932 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170067 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Gei\u00df KR, Jester I, Falke W, Hamm M, Waag KL | title = The effect of a taurine-containing drink on performance in 10 endurance-athletes | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 7 | issue = 1 | pages = 45\u201356 | date = February 1994 | pmid = 24185972 | doi = 10.1007/BF00808445 }}</ref> performance. Performance during prolonged driving is increased after consumption of Red Bull.<ref name=\":1\" /> Other tests for physical performance showed results such as increased endurance and power. Red Bull energy drink increased upper body muscle endurance during repeated Wingate tests in young healthy adults.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Forbes SC, Candow DG, Little JP, Magnus C, Chilibeck PD | title = Effect of Red Bull energy drink on repeated Wingate cycle performance and bench-press muscle endurance | journal = International Journal of Sport Nutrition and Exercise Metabolism | volume = 17 | issue = 5 | pages = 433\u201344 | date = October 2007 | pmid = 18046053 | doi = 10.1123/ijsnem.17.5.433 }}</ref> Excessive or repeated consumption of energy drinks can lead to cardiac and psychiatric conditions.<ref name=\"pmid25818530\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sanchis-Gomar F, Pareja-Galeano H, Cervellin G, Lippi G, Earnest CP | title = Energy drink overconsumption in adolescents: implications for arrhythmias and other cardiovascular events | journal = The Canadian Journal of Cardiology | volume = 31 | issue = 5 | pages = 572\u20135 | date = May 2015 | pmid = 25818530 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/j.cjca.2014.12.019 | hdl = 11268/3906 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid25622514\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Petit A, Karila L, Lejoyeux M | title = [Abuse of energy drinks: does it pose a risk?] | journal = Presse M\u00e9dicale | volume = 44 | issue = 3 | pages = 261\u201370 | date = March 2015 | pmid = 25622514 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/j.lpm.2014.07.029 }}</ref>\n\nThe [[European Food Safety Authority]] (EFSA) concluded that exposure to taurine and glucuronolactone at the levels presently used in energy drinks is not a safety concern.<ref name=EFSA935>{{cite journal |url=http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/efsajournal/pub/935 |title=The use of taurine and D-glucurono-\u03b3-lactone as constituents of the so-called 'energy' drinks |journal=The EFSA Journal |year=2009 |volume=935 |issue=2 |pages=1\u201331 |author=EFSA Panel on Food Additives and Nutrient Sources added to Food |doi=10.2903/j.efsa.2009.935|doi-access=free }}</ref> In a separate analysis, they also concluded that there is insufficient evidence to support a number of commercial health claims about taurine.<ref name=EFSA2009>Scientific Opinion on the substantiation of health claims related to taurine and protection of DNA, proteins and lipids from oxidative damage (ID 612,1658, 1959), energy-yielding metabolism (ID 614), and delay in the onset of fatigue and enhancement of physical performance (ID 1660) pursuant to Article 13(1) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, European Food Safety Authority 2009, https://efsa.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.2903/j.efsa.2009.1260</ref> A review published in 2008 found no documented reports of negative or positive health effects associated with the amount of [[taurine]] used in energy drinks, including Red Bull. The review also states that though the caffeine and sugar levels in the energy drink are comparable to those present in coffee and fruit juice respectively, these levels have been shown to cause adverse health effects.<ref name=McQueen>{{cite journal | vauthors = Clauson KA, Shields KM, McQueen CE, Persad N | title = Safety issues associated with commercially available energy drinks | journal = Journal of the American Pharmacists Association | volume = 48 | issue = 3 | pages = e55\u201363; quiz e64\u20137 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18595815 | doi = 10.1331/JAPhA.2008.07055 }}</ref>\n \nIn its scientific opinion on the safety of caffeine of 2015, the EFSA concluded that \"consumption of other constituents of [[energy drinks]] at concentrations commonly present in such beverages would not affect the safety of single doses of caffeine up to 200 mg.\" Also, the consumption of alcohol, leading to a blood alcohol content of about 0.08%, would, according to the EFSA, not affect the safety of single doses of caffeine up to 200&nbsp;mg. Up to these levels of intake, caffeine is unlikely to mask the subjective perception of alcohol intoxication. Habitual use of caffeine up to 400&nbsp;mg per day does not.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAccording to [[SAMHSA]], \"the number of emergency department (ED) visits\" among people over age 12 related to energy drinks doubled between 2007 and 2011 in the US (from 10,068 to 20,783).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/spot124-energy-drinks-2014.pdf |title=1 in 10 Energy Drink-Related Emergency Department Visits Results in Hospitalization |publisher=Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration |access-date=9 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Caffeine content===\nThe [[caffeine]] content of a single can of Red Bull is approximately 80\u201340&nbsp;mg{{\\}}250&nbsp;mL (32\u201315&nbsp;mg{{\\}}100&nbsp;mL).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://coffeetea.about.com/od/caffeine/gr/redbull.htm |title=Red Bull caffeine beverage review |publisher=[[About.com]] |date=22 October 2009 |access-date=2012-05-29 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415002317/http://coffeetea.about.com/od/caffeine/gr/redbull.htm |archive-date=15 April 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/beverages/7399/2 |title=Nutrition Facts and Analysis for Energy drink, RED BULL, with added caffeine, niacin, pantothenic acid, vitamins B6 and B12 |publisher=Cond\u00e9 Nast |access-date=2012-05-29}}</ref><ref name=\"can photo\"/> This is about the same as one i.e. half a cup of coffee, or slightly less or more depending on the brewing method and country of production.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://coffeefaq.com/site/node/22 |title=How much caffeine is there in [drink/food/pill]? |publisher=Coffeefaq.com |date=15 January 2006 |access-date=2012-09-24|first=Daniel |last=Owen}}{{self-published source|date=April 2013}}</ref>{{self-published inline|date=April 2013}} The caffeine level in Red Bull varies depending on country, as some countries have legal restrictions on how much caffeine is allowed in drinks. As is the case with other caffeinated beverages, Red Bull drinkers may experience [[Energy drink#Adverse effects|adverse effects]] as a result of overuse. Excessive consumption may induce mild to moderate [[euphoria (emotion)|euphoria]] primarily caused by stimulant properties of caffeine and may also induce agitation, [[anxiety (mood)|anxiety]], irritability and [[insomnia]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Alford C, Cox H, Wescott R | title = The effects of red bull energy drink on human performance and mood | journal = Amino Acids | volume = 21 | issue = 2 | pages = 139\u201350 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11665810 | doi = 10.1007/s007260170021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Richards G, Smith AP | title = A Review of Energy Drinks and Mental Health, with a Focus on Stress, Anxiety, and Depression | journal = Journal of Caffeine Research | volume = 6 | issue = 2 | pages = 49\u201363 | date = June 2016 | pmid = 27274415 | pmc = 4892220 | doi = 10.1089/jcr.2015.0033 }}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nThe general population of healthy adults is not at risk for potential adverse effects from caffeine if they limit their consumption to 400&nbsp;mg per day, which is the equivalent of 5 standard cans, with one can being 250ml in volume.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/fn-an/securit/addit/caf/index-eng.php |title=It's Your Health \u2013 Caffeine |publisher=Health Canada |date=13 April 2012 |access-date=24 November 2014}}</ref> Consumption of a single energy drink will not lead to excessive caffeine intake.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Nawrot\">{{cite journal |doi=10.1192/apt.11.6.432 |name-list-format=vanc|title=Neuropsychiatric effects of caffeine |year=2005 |last1=Winston |first1=AP |journal=Advances in Psychiatric Treatment |volume=11 |issue=6 |pages=432\u2013439|doi-access=free }}</ref> Adverse effects associated with caffeine consumption in amounts greater than 400&nbsp;mg include nervousness, irritability, sleeplessness, increased urination, abnormal heart rhythms ([[Heart arrhythmia|arrhythmia]]), and [[dyspepsia]]. Consumption also has been known to cause [[pupil dilation]] when taken with certain antidepressants or [[SSRI]]s.<ref name=\"Nawrot\" /><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Jin MJ, Yoon CH, Ko HJ, Kim HM, Kim AS, Moon HN, Jung SP | title = The Relationship of Caffeine Intake with Depression, Anxiety, Stress, and Sleep in Korean Adolescents | journal = Korean Journal of Family Medicine | volume = 37 | issue = 2 | pages = 111\u20136 | date = March 2016 | pmid = 27073610 | pmc = 4826990 | doi = 10.4082/kjfm.2016.37.2.111 }}</ref> Caffeine dosage is not required to be on the product label for food in the United States, unlike drugs, but some advocates are urging the FDA to change this practice. (Red Bull voluntarily lists the caffeine content in each can along with the ingredient list.)<ref>[https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94973371 Warning: Energy Drinks Contain Caffeine] by Allison Aubrey. Morning Edition, National Public Radio, 24 September 2008.</ref>\n\n==Market approval and legal status==\nAuthorities in France, [[Denmark]], and [[Norway]] initially kept Red Bull from being sold domestically.<ref name=\"2004CourtRuling\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/health-news/European-court-backs-ban-on-red-bull-over-health-concerns-68019.html|title=European court backs ban on Red Bull over health concerns|date=7 February 2004|last=Frith|first=Maxine|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|access-date=2010-11-22|location=London}}</ref> However, {{as of|2014|lc=y}}, it is on sale in all 28 [[member states of the European Union]] and in more than 167 countries around the world.\n\nThe French food safety agency was concerned about [[taurine]]. A Red Bull drink that did not contain taurine was introduced. The French refusal of market approval was challenged by the European Commission, and partially upheld by the [[European Court of Justice]] in 2004.<ref name=\"2004CourtRuling\" /> The French food safety agency relented in 2008, because it was unable to prove a definite health risk, taurine-related or not.<ref name=\"FranceBanEnd\">{{Cite news|title=France ends 12-year ban on energy drink Red Bull|location=Paris|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=15 July 2008|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL1576964720080715|access-date=2010-11-22}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, the Kuwaiti [[Ministry of Commerce (Kuwait)|Ministry of Commerce]] banned Red Bull for people under 16 after it had allegedly caused heart attacks for a 16-year-old and a 21-year-old national squash team player.<ref>{{cite web | title = Kuwaiti player dies after taking energy drinks |publisher = GulfNews| url = http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/kuwait/kuwaiti-player-dies-after-taking-energy-drinks-1.1184369 |author=Habib Toumi, Bureau Chief|date=16 May 2013| access-date = 2014-07-05  }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = KUNA : Decisions regulating sale of energy drinks issued \u2013 Economics \u2013 21/10/2012 | url = http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2269729&language=en |date= 21 October 2012|access-date = 2014-07-05 |publisher=[[Kuwait News Agency]] (KUNA)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | script-title=ar:\u0643\u0648\u0646\u0627 : \u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0642\u0631\u0627\u0631\u0627 \u064a\u0646\u0638\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u062a\u0627\u062c \u0648\u0639\u0631\u0636 \u0648\u0628\u064a\u0639 \u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0642\u0629 \u2013 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u2013 21 October 2012 | url = http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2269682&Language=ar | date= 21 October 2012|access-date = 2014-07-05 |publisher=[[Kuwait News Agency]] (KUNA)|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | script-title=ar:\"\u0627\u0644\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0631\u0629\": \u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0642\u0629 \u0645\u0645\u0646\u0648\u0639\u0629 \u0644\u0645\u0646 \u062f\u0648\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0640 16 | publisher=[[Al-Qabas newspaper]] | url=http://www.alqabas.com.kw/node/244222 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708011326/http://www.alqabas.com.kw/node/244222 | url-status=dead | archive-date=2014-07-08 | date=21 October 2012 | access-date=2014-07-05 | language=ar }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Red Bull and a crisis in Kuwait that hasn't hit the headlines |publisher= Alex of Arabia's Blog | url = http://alexofarabia.com/2013/04/20/red-bull-and-a-crisis-in-kuwait-that-hasnt-hit-the-headlines/ | access-date = 2014-07-05 |date= 2013-04-20 }}\n</ref><ref name=\"Red Bull Kuwait Loses Millions\">{{cite web|title=Red Bull Kuwait Loses Millions|url=http://www.q8critic.com/red-bull-kuwait-loses-millions|publisher=Q8Critic|date=24 October 2012|access-date=2013-06-28|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625023916/http://www.q8critic.com/red-bull-kuwait-loses-millions/|archive-date=25 June 2013}}</ref><ref>http://omarker.com/?p=15727{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Litigation==\nIn 2013, Red Bull told the Redwell Brewery, a [[Norfolk]] [[micro brewery]], to change its name or face legal action, because it sounded too similar to Red Bull. The eight-man brewery in [[Norwich]] was told its name could \"confuse\" customers and \"tarnish\" its trademark.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-norfolk-23697138 |title=Red Bull pursues Redwell brewery in Norwich over name |work=[[BBC News]] |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref> The two companies reached a settlement permitting Redwell to continue using its name.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-norfolk-23705255 |title=Red Bull ends dispute with Redwell brewery in Norwich |work=[[BBC News]] |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=2013-11-13}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Red Bull faced a US$13&nbsp;million settlement addressing two consumer class action lawsuits in the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.law360.com/articles/563228/red-bull-puts-up-13m-to-settle-false-advertising-suit|title=Red Bull Puts Up $13M To Settle False Advertising Suit \u2013 Law360|website=www.law360.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> The listed plaintiffs were Benjamin Careathers, David Wolf, and Miguel Almarez<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://topclassactions.com/lawsuit-settlements/lawsuit-news/36145-red-bull-agrees-13m-false-advertising-class-action-settlement/|title=Red Bull Agrees to $13M False Advertising Class Action Settlement|date=4 August 2014|work=Top Class Actions|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> who sued the company for Red Bull's marketing and labeling, claiming that the company violated \"express warranty and unjust enrichment\" since their products were first launched by claiming performance-enhancing benefits from the drink's ingredients which were not substantiated by scientific studies.<ref name=bevnet>{{cite web|title=Red Bull to Pay $13 Million|url=http://www.bevnet.com/news/2014/red-bull-to-pay-13-million-for-false-advertising-settlement|website=bevnet.com|publisher=Law360.|access-date=2014-10-21|date=2014-08-05}}</ref> The court hearing took place the morning of 1 May 2015 in an attempt to determine approval for the settlement. Customers that submitted claims then have the opportunity to receive a US$10 cash reimbursement or product option of US$15 in Red Bull products<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/drink-red-bull-you-may-have-10-coming-to-you/ |title=Drink Red Bull? You may have $10 coming to you |publisher=cbsnews.com |date=9 October 2014 |access-date=2015-02-16}}</ref> within 150 days of the approved appeals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/29550003 |title=So Red Bull doesn't actually 'give you wings' |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=9 October 2014 |access-date=2014-11-03}}</ref>  Contrary to false reports from some [[news media|news outlets]], the lawsuit was not about the drink failing to give the consumer actual wings.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[Snopes]] |url=https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/red-bulls-wings/ |title=Fact check: Red Bull does (not) give you wings |last=O\u2019Reilly |first=Laura |date=8 October 2014 |access-date=10 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Advertising==\n[[File:Max_Verstappen_(36132602681).jpg|thumb|[[Max Verstappen]] in the [[Red Bull RB13]], the 2017 Formula One car of the [[Red Bull Racing]] Team]]\n[[File:Red Bull Cobra G\u00f3raszka 7.JPG|thumb|Red Bull's [[AH-1 Cobra|TAH-1F Cobra]] helicopter assembled by [[Chuck Aaron]], owned by the [[Flying Bulls]]]]\n[[File:North American B-25J Mitchell Red Bull (The Flying Bulls) N6123C (9292015992).jpg|thumb|right|A Red Bull [[North American B-25 Mitchell]]]]\nSince 1997, Red Bull has been making commercials bearing its slogan \"Red Bull gives you wings,\"<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/1133348.stm | title=Energy drink claims rejected| date=2001-01-24}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull's international marketing campaign targets young men mostly with [[extreme sports]]. These range from mountain biking,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mbaction.com/uncategorized/red-bull-rampage-recap|title=Red Bull Rampage Recap|last=sean|website=Mountain Bike Action Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08|date=2017-02-05}}</ref> BMX,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/photos/gallery/_/id/9362075/image/7/aj-anaya-red-bull-framed-reactions-bmx-park-competition-amsterdam|title=Drew Bezanson wins Red Bull Framed Reactions BMX Park comp|work=XGames|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> motocross,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://motocross.transworld.net/videos/2017-red-bull-ktm-team-intro/#K83xyH80VQMW3xvR.97|title=2017 Red Bull KTM {{!}} Team Intro {{!}} Transworld Motocross|date=18 December 2016|work=Transworld Motocross|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> windsurfing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pwaworldtour.com/index.php?id=35&tx_news_pi1%5Bnews%5D=3694&tx_news_pi1%5Bcontroller%5D=News&tx_news_pi1%5Baction%5D=detail&cHash=a6e5007e8e6cb2f3da520cf203fc4183|title=Red Bull Storm Chase|last=(PWA)|first=Professional Windsurfing Association|work=PWA World Tour|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> snowboarding,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.snowboarder.com/tag/red-bull-snowboarding/|title=Red Bull Snowboarding {{!}} Snowboarder Magazine.|website=Snowboarder Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> skateboarding,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skateboarding.transworld.net/tag/red-bull-skateboarding/|title=red bull skateboarding {{!}} TransWorld SKATEboarding|website=TransWorld SKATEboarding|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> kayaking,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/chasing-niagara-falls-in-a-kayak|title=Chasing Niagara Falls in a Kayak {{!}} VICE Sports|work=VICE Sports|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309072917/https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/chasing-niagara-falls-in-a-kayak|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> rowing,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/?job_id=4239|title=Red Bull High Stakes \u2013 Overview|website=www.regattacentral.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> wakeboarding,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wakeboardingmag.com/red-bull-wake-steel-2016|title=Red Bull Wake of Steel 2016|work=Wakeboarding Magazine|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> cliff-diving,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/red-bull-cliff-diving-world-202700299.html|title=Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series Announces 2017 Schedule|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309072250/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/red-bull-cliff-diving-world-202700299.html|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[parkour]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://greece.greekreporter.com/2016/10/02/bart-van-der-linden-wins-parkour-red-bull-art-of-motion-in-santorini-video/|title=...Wins Parkour Red Bull Art of Motion in Santorini (video) {{!}} GreekReporter.com|last=Kolasa-Sikiaridi|first=Kerry|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> surfing,<ref>{{Citation|title=RED BULL QIANTANG: SURFING SHOOTOUT|url=http://www.surfline.com/video/contests/red-bull-qiantang-surfing-shootout_95487|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> skating,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visitsaintpaul.com/things-to-do/winter-fun/red-bull-crashed-ice-championship/|title=Red Bull Crashed Ice Championship in Saint Paul, MN \u2013 Visit Saint Paul|website=www.visitsaintpaul.com|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309061655/http://www.visitsaintpaul.com/things-to-do/winter-fun/red-bull-crashed-ice-championship/|archive-date=9 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> freestyle motocross,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://iq.intel.com/red-bull-x-fighters/|title=Real-Time Data Tech Dazzles Red Bull X-Fighters Fans|date=22 June 2016|work=iQ by Intel|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916210645/http://iq.intel.com/red-bull-x-fighters/|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> rallycross,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.racer.com/international/world-rally/item/138614-red-bull-global-rallycross-new-england-set-for-june|title=Red Bull Global Rallycross New England set for June|last=GRC|website=www.racer.com|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308145010/http://www.racer.com/international/world-rally/item/138614-red-bull-global-rallycross-new-england-set-for-june|archive-date=8 March 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Formula&nbsp;1 racing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/red-bull-positive-rb13-can-challenge-mercedes-in-f1-2017-879644/|title=Red Bull \"positive\" RB13 can challenge Mercedes in F1 2017|work=Motorsport.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> [[NASCAR]] racing,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.archrival.com/work/29/red-bull-racing-in-nascar/|title=Archrival {{!}} Red Bull Racing in NASCAR|work=Archrival|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> to breakdancing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.axs.com/redbull-flying-bach-tour-brings-bach-and-breakdancing-to-dallas-in-201-106667|title=Redbull Flying Bach tour brings Bach and breakdancing to Dallas in 2017|work=AXS|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> Red Bull uses music and videogames, and has enlisted celebrities, such as [[Eminem]] (sponsoring the Red Bull \"EmSee Battle Rap championships\").<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/calling-battle-rappers-enter-red-bull-emsee-miami-and-win-a-trip-to-the-finals-in-atlanta-6462178|title=Calling Battle Rappers! Enter Red Bull EmSee Miami and Win a Trip to the Finals in Atlanta|last=Pajot|first=S.|date=3 November 2011|work=Miami New Times|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> It hosts events like art shows and the \"[[Red Bull Flugtag]]\" (German for \"flight day\" or \"flying day\").<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/life/2017/03/07/red-bulls-high-flying-flugtag-competition-return-nashville/98834598/|title=Red Bull's high-flying Flugtag competition to return to Nashville|work=The Tennessean|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\nRed Bull owns football teams, with clubs in Austria,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/austria/fc-red-bull-salzburg/165/|title=Austria \u2013 FC Salzburg \u2013 Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news \u2013 Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> Germany,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/12/16/rb-leipzigs-bundesliga-debut-is-like-a-fairy-tale-in-which-the-bad-guys-are-winning/|title=Analysis {{!}} RB Leipzig's Bundesliga debut is like a fairy tale in which the bad guys are winning|website=Washington Post|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> the United States,<ref name=\":2\" /> and Brazil<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/brazil/red-bull-brasil/14538/|title=Brazil \u2013 Red Bull Brasil \u2013 Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news \u2013 Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> featuring the Red Bull trademark in their names. By associating the drink's image with these activities, the company seeks to promote a \"cool\" public image and raise brand power. The energy drink has created a market for over 150 related types of products.<ref>{{cite web|title=RED BULL HISTORY|url=http://www.speedace.info/red_bull.htm|website=speedace.info|publisher=Electrick Publications.|access-date=2012-07-27}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[PlayStation 3]]'s social gaming platform, [[PlayStation Home]], Red Bull developed its own [[List of PlayStation Home Game Spaces#Non-gaming Company Spaces|in-game island]], specifically advertising its energy drink and the [[Red Bull Air Race]] event (for which the space is named) released in January 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/red-bull-becomes-first-brand-playstation-home/890098|title=Red Bull becomes first brand on PlayStation Home|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref> In late November 2009, Red Bull produced two new spaces, the [[Red Bull Illume]] space, and the Red Bull Beach space featuring the [[Red Bull Flugtag]], both released on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kotaku.com/5443106/red-bull-gives-playstation-home-new-things-to-do/|title=Red Bull Gives PlayStation Home New Things To Do|last=Fahey|first=Mike|work=Kotaku|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704153417/https://kotaku.com/5443106/red-bull-gives-playstation-home-new-things-to-do/|archive-date=4 July 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In January 2012, Red Bull released its first personal space called the \"Red Bull House of Skate\" featuring an indoor skate park.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yourpshome.net/showcase/red-bull-house-of-skate.90/|title=Red Bull House of Skate|work=YourPSHome.net|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn the [[App Store (iOS)|Apple App store]] Red Bull also has a few apps which include: RedBull.com, [[Red Bull TV]], The Red Bulletin, RBMA Radio, Red Bull iFunk, Wings For Life- Selfie Run. As well as some games on the app store which are: Bike Unchained, Red Bull Kart Fighter 3, Red Bull Air Race The Game, Red Bull Racers.<ref>{{Cite web|title = iTunes \u2013 Browse the top free apps on the App Store \u2013 Apple|url = https://www.apple.com/itunes/charts/free-apps/|website = Apple|access-date = 2016-02-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, the company enlisted Adrian Newey to design a prototype racing car, the [[Red Bull X2010]], for the videogame ''[[Gran Turismo 5]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gtvault.com/gt5/setup-view/s_sid::9231/Gran-Turismo-Red-Bull-X2011-Prototype--11/|title=GTVault \u2013 Gran Turismo 5Setup for|website=www.gtvault.com|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n\n===Red Bull House of Art===\nThe '''Red Bull House of Art''' is an art fellowship program that was launched by Red Bull.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Abbey-Lambertz|first1=Kate|title=Red Bull House of Art Bolsters Detroit Scene By Giving Artists on the Verge A Leg Up (VIDEO)|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/red-bull-house-of-art-detroit-cycle-5_n_3720077.html|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2015-01-24|date=7 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=freep>{{cite news|last1=Hammerstein|first1=BJ|title=Detroit artist star of new Red Bull ad|url=http://archive.freep.com/article/20140125/NEWS01/301250052/Detroit-made-Red-Bull-ad-to-air-during-Grammys|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|access-date=2015-01-24}}</ref> The program is held in multiple cities, most notably the Red Bull House of Art programs in Detroit, Michigan and [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]], and the program typically consists of a three-month period during which time six to eight participants will create new artwork with the intent to display it in a final exhibition.<ref name=TOB>{{cite web|last1=Rigby|first1=Claire|title=Red Bull Station opens up downtown|url=http://www.timeout.com.br/sao-paulo/en/art/features/458/red-bull-station-opens-up-downtown|publisher=Time Out Brazil|access-date=2015-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128131911/http://www.timeout.com.br/sao-paulo/en/art/features/458/red-bull-station-opens-up-downtown|archive-date=28 January 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=mt1>{{cite news|last1=DeVito|first1=Lee|title=Meet the creative minds behind the Red Bull House of Art's Cycle 8|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/detroit/meet-the-creative-minds-behind-the-red-bull-house-of-arts-cycle-8/Content?oid=2214656|newspaper=Metro Times|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref> During the fellowship the artists receive unlimited access to the galleries and a [[stipend]] for art supplies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Trevino|first1=Jessica J.|title=Meet the 6 local artists featured in the Red Bull House of Art exhibit|url=http://www.freep.com/article/20140806/ENT05/308060039/red-bull-house-exhibit-detroit|newspaper=Detroit Free Press|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe program has received criticism as being an \"elaborate advertising scheme\",<ref>{{cite web|last1=DeVito|first1=Lee|title=Red Bull House of Art|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/detroit/red-bull-house-of-art/Content?oid=2145533|publisher=MetroTimes|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref> as some of the artwork has been used in Red Bull advertising campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lacy|first1=Eric|title=Grammys 2014: Watch Detroit Red Bull House of Art 'City of Soldiers' commercial aired during show|url=http://www.mlive.com/entertainment/detroit/index.ssf/2014/01/grammys_2014_watch_detroit_red.html|publisher=MLive|access-date=24 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Sports sponsorships and acquisitions===\n{{seealsocat|Red Bull sports teams}}\n* [[Red Bull Racing]]\u2014a [[Formula One]] team based in [[Milton Keynes]], England, World Constructor's Championship winner of 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013, and produced the car for the 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013 F1 World Champion [[Sebastian Vettel]].\n* [[Scuderia AlphaTauri]] (Named after Red Bull's fashion brand [[AlphaTauri (fashion brand)|AlphaTauri]]): Another Formula One team based in [[Faenza]], Italy, considered Red Bull's \u201cjunior\u201d team\n* [[RB Leipzig]]: a [[Association football|football]] club currently playing in the German [[Bundesliga|1. Bundesliga]]\n* [[New York Red Bulls]]: a [[Association football|football]] franchise competing in [[Major League Soccer]] of the United States.\n* [[Red Bull Sailing Team]]: an [[Extreme Sailing Series]] racing team.\n* [[Team Red Bull]]: a Toyota racing team competing in the U.S.-based stock car racing competition [[NASCAR]] Red Bull Racing Team competed in NASCAR beginning in 2007. The team ceased operations after the Sprint Cup Series' 2011 season.\n* [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]]: an Austrian football club based in Salzburg and competing in the [[Austrian Bundesliga]]\n* [[EC Red Bull Salzburg]]: a member of the [[Austrian Hockey League]] based in Salzburg, Austria\n* [[EHC Red Bull M\u00fcnchen]]: a member of the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] based in [[Munich]], Germany\n* [[Red Bull Brasil]]: a football club which played in the Brazilian [[Campeonato Paulista]] based in [[Campinas]], Brazil before merging with [[Bragantino]] in 2019.\n[[File:Shane van Gisbergen at Sydney Motorsport Park.jpg|thumb|200px|2017 [[Holden Commodore]] #97 of [[Shane van Gisbergen]] of the [[Triple Eight Race Engineering|Red Bull Holden Racing Team]]]]\n* [[Triple Eight Race Engineering|Red Bull Holden Racing Team]] \u2013 a [[Supercars Championship|Supercars]] team run by Triple Eight Race Engineering, manufacturer of cars 88 driven by seven-time champion [[Jamie Whincup]] and 97 driven by [[2016 International V8 Supercars Championship|2016]] champion [[Shane van Gisbergen]] \u2013 Red Bull had sponsored the team as Red Bull Racing Australia, from [[2013 International V8 Supercars Championship|2013]] until [[2017 International V8 Supercars Championship|2017]], when the team was given sole factory backing from [[Holden]], rebranding as the Red Bull Holden Racing Team.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.supercars.com/news/championship/holden-commits-to-supercars/|title=Holden commits to Supercars {{!}} Supercars|work=Supercars|access-date=2017-10-15}}</ref>\n* Red Bull Racing Brasil, a [[Stock Car Brasil]] team, from 2007 to 2017.\n* [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]], a team competing in [[Grand Prix motorcycle racing|MotoGP]]. \n* [[Red Bull Ghana]]: was a Ghanaian professional football club located in Sogakope that played in the [[Ghana Football Leagues|Poly Tank Division One League]].\n* [[\u0160koda Motorsport]] [[rallying|rally]] team\n* [[Red Bulls]], a [[League of Legends]] team currently playing in the [[League of Legends Challenger Series#Europe|European League of Legends Challenger Series]]\n* Esports team [[OG Dota 2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.redbull.com/za-en/og-announcement |title=OG and the rise of player centred teams |publisher=redbull.com |access-date=2017-08-02}}</ref>\n\n===Sponsorships===\n[[File:Audi Abt Sportsline.jpg|thumb|Audi A4 DTM, which won the Manufacturers' championship in 2004]]\n[[File:Kimi R\u00e4ikk\u00f6nen - 2010 Rally Bulgaria.jpg|thumb|The Citro\u00ebn rally car, which won the manufacturers' title in 2008, 2009 and 2010.]]\n[[File:Mika Kallio.jpg|thumb|A Red Bull sponsored track racing bike]]\n[[File:Hangar7-01.jpg|thumb|A Sauber C15 from 1995 in display at Red Bull Hangar-7]]\n[[File:Dakar car 2007.jpg|thumb|A VW Touareg during the Dakar Rally, which won the event in 2009, 2010 and 2011]]\n[[File:Antonio_Cairoli_ITA_FMI_Yamaha_FIM_MX_Mallory_Park_2008_R6a.jpg|thumb|Antonio Cairoli, which won the motocross world championship in 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2017]]\n* [[100 Thieves]]\n* [[Abt Sportsline]] \n* [[Arrows Grand Prix International|Arrows]] F1 team from 2001 to 2002\n* [[Audi Sport]] for the A4 DTM\n* Batalla de los Gallos\n* [[Cac\u00e1 Bueno]]'s speed record Vectra\n* [[Carlin Motorsport]] Dallara-Renault\n* [[Citro\u00ebn World Rally Team]] (2008\u20132012)\n* [[Cloud9]] ''League of Legends'' eSports team\n* [[EKS RX]]\n* [[Ford Fiesta WRC]]\n* [[G2 eSports]]''League of Legends'' eSports team\n* [[Hansen Motorsport]] rallycross team\n* [[Hyundai Genesis Coupe]] Pikes Peak edition\n* [[Hyundai Veloster]] rallycross car\n* [[Kamaz]] Dakar rally trucks\n* [[JMB Racing]] Maserati MC12 GT\n* [[KTM]] road, MXGP and Dakar rally bikes\n* Red Bull [[Ajo Motorsport]]\n* Red Bull Youth America's Cup\n* [[Repsol Honda|Repsol Honda Team]]\n* [[OG (eSports)|OG]] ''Dota 2'' eSports team\n* Oracle Team USA\n* [[Olsbergs MSE]] Ford rallycross team\n* [[Peugeot 208]] T16\n* [[Peugeot 2008 DKR]] (2015)\n* [[Sauber]] F1 team (1995\u20132004)\n* [[SEAT Sport]] WTCC team\n* [[\u0160koda Fabia S2000]]\n* [[Ten Kate Racing|Red Bull Honda World Superbike Team]]\n* [[Volkswagen Passat]] [[DARPA Grand Challenge]] edition\n* Andrew Dickson, pro BMX rider \n* [[Volkswagen Polo R WRC]]\n* [[Volkswagen Race Touareg]] Dakar edition\n* [[Volkswagen Touareg|Volkswagen V10 TDI Touaregs Pikes Peak edition]]\n\n===Endorsements===\nIn 2009, Red Bull added mainstream sport athletes to its roster of endorsements, which also includes persons involved in non-sporting activities.\n\n* [[Reggie Bush]], US NFL athlete announced at the [[Super Bowl XLIV|2009 Super Bowl]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espnmag/story?id=3873150 |title=Reggie Bush Goes to Red Bull&nbsp;\u2013 ESPN The Magazine |publisher=Sports.espn.go.com |access-date=2009-06-22|date=2009-01-30 }}</ref>\n*[[Ryan Dungey]] American Supercross, Motocross rider for [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]].\n**\n*[[Marvin Musquin]] French Supercross, Motocross rider for [[Red Bull KTM Factory Racing]].\n**\n* [[Dani Pedrosa]], [[Marc M\u00e1rquez]], [[John Reynolds (motorcycle racer)|John Reynolds]], [[Andrea Dovizioso]], [[Casey Stoner]], and [[Nicky Hayden]]\n* [[Red Bull Junior Team]], a program which sponsors young drivers competing in [[Single seater racing car|single seater racing]]. Since 2001 many young drivers developed careers in professional motorsport, with 13 participants having competed in Formula One, including quadruple F1 world champion [[Sebastian Vettel]], [[Daniel Ricciardo]], and [[Max Verstappen]]\n* Skijumpers [[Gregor Schlierenzauer]], [[Thomas Morgenstern]], [[Adam Ma\u0142ysz]], and [[Andreas Goldberger]], snowboarders [[Mark McMorris]], [[Torah Bright]] and [[Nathan Johnstone]], and skiers [[Kaya Turski]], [[Lindsey Vonn]], [[Axel Lund Svindal]] and [[Alexis Pinturault]].\n* [[Dion Phaneuf]] NHL defenseman\n* Young professional golfer [[Rickie Fowler]].\n* Racing driver [[Andrew Jordan (racing driver)|Andrew Jordan]].\n* Drift racing driver [[\"Mad\" Mike 